WEBVTT

00:08.209 --> 00:18.250
<i> ♪</i>

00:40.574 --> 00:42.107
So, playing with
this year's concept,

00:42.143 --> 00:43.542
"The Light of Christmas,"

00:43.577 --> 00:49.181
I went from day to night,
light to dark, ending here.

00:49.250 --> 00:51.583
Or, alternatively, we could
reverse the order.

00:51.619 --> 00:53.652
Start here, and then
move towards the...

00:53.687 --> 00:55.154
The order doesn't matter.

00:55.189 --> 00:57.122
I like what you've captured.

00:57.158 --> 00:58.424
You do?

00:58.459 --> 01:00.893
The architectural aspect
is super high-concept,

01:00.928 --> 01:02.694
and well, your point of view
as a photographer

01:02.730 --> 01:04.063
has always been unique.

01:04.131 --> 01:05.764
That's why we've hired you,
for, what...

01:05.800 --> 01:07.666
Six assignments, so far.

01:07.735 --> 01:08.934
But this?

01:08.969 --> 01:12.237
This is the magazine insert
for Christmas Day.

01:12.306 --> 01:14.373
It's not only a great
portfolio piece,

01:14.442 --> 01:17.309
it's also, as you know, a chance
to join our staff.

01:17.378 --> 01:18.510
I know.

01:18.546 --> 01:20.079
I know. I can't believe
an opening came up.

01:20.114 --> 01:21.380
And since it showed up
over the holidays,

01:21.415 --> 01:22.881
we thought, why not offer it
to the photographer

01:22.950 --> 01:24.983
who lands the Christmas spread?

01:25.019 --> 01:26.318
I love that.

01:26.387 --> 01:28.854
And I'm very grateful to be
in the running.

01:28.889 --> 01:31.957
Look, I'm a fan of these,
uh, I am, but...

01:31.992 --> 01:33.759
Is that a maybe?

01:33.794 --> 01:35.894
We'll see what the chief says.

01:35.930 --> 01:36.929
Thank you.

01:37.565 --> 01:38.397
Oh.

01:39.333 --> 01:40.466
Christmas or not,

01:40.501 --> 01:42.968
you'll absolutely get
our volume discount.

01:43.003 --> 01:43.802
Okay, great.

01:43.871 --> 01:45.270
I'll send our rates over now.

01:45.306 --> 01:47.573
Merry Christmas.

01:47.641 --> 01:50.275
Please tell me he said yes.

01:50.311 --> 01:51.677
He said it's up to the chief.

01:51.745 --> 01:52.578
How's that?

01:52.613 --> 01:53.645
That's great!

01:53.714 --> 01:54.346
Is it?

01:54.381 --> 01:55.414
Yeah.

01:55.449 --> 01:57.616
Anne loves your work.

01:57.651 --> 02:00.252
And when you start here,
just think.

02:00.287 --> 02:01.887
Lunches all the time.

02:01.922 --> 02:03.522
How fun is that?

02:03.557 --> 02:06.792
I know, I just... I don't want
to get too excited just yet.

02:06.827 --> 02:07.759
You know?

02:07.795 --> 02:09.228
You're the hardest worker
I know.

02:09.263 --> 02:11.096
You're gonna land this spread,
and the position.

02:11.132 --> 02:13.065
Just, is it what you want?

02:13.100 --> 02:15.000
It's a lot of 9:00 to 5:00.

02:16.971 --> 02:20.739
Yeah, I wish I could say I was
cut out for the hustle, but...

02:20.774 --> 02:22.875
9:00 to 5:00 sounds pretty good
right about now.

02:22.910 --> 02:24.109
You know?

02:24.145 --> 02:25.611
Maybe it would be good
to change up the pace.

02:25.646 --> 02:27.246
Hey, it might even give you
some time to go on that date

02:27.281 --> 02:29.615
with my neighbour.

02:29.683 --> 02:31.850
What? He's cute.

02:31.886 --> 02:33.652
I'm sure he is, I just...

02:33.687 --> 02:36.288
...Haven't been on a date
in way too long?

02:36.323 --> 02:39.258
...Need to get through this next
week first.

02:39.326 --> 02:42.794
How are you feeling?

02:42.830 --> 02:44.463
About going back to the Cape?

02:44.498 --> 02:47.399
Your family's summer home.

02:47.434 --> 02:52.171
Uh, I don't know.

02:52.206 --> 02:54.740
I mean, I... I used to love
going there.

02:54.775 --> 02:56.708
And how long's it been?

02:56.744 --> 02:57.910
Thirteen years.

02:57.978 --> 03:00.846
But you have a lot of great
memories there.

03:00.881 --> 03:02.247
Yeah.

03:02.283 --> 03:03.582
Yeah, every summer.

03:03.617 --> 03:05.851
But it's gonna be great.

03:05.886 --> 03:08.520
It's where my Dad met Helen,
they're gonna retire there.

03:08.556 --> 03:11.089
I've never been for Christmas
or a wedding, so...

03:11.125 --> 03:12.424
Yeah, that's the spirit.

03:12.459 --> 03:16.628
Just go, relax,
and enjoy Christmas.

03:16.664 --> 03:20.098
Two double lattes, please.

03:20.901 --> 03:22.401
Ta-Dah.

03:22.436 --> 03:23.368
Wait, what's this?

03:23.404 --> 03:24.870
I thought we said
no presents.

03:24.905 --> 03:27.172
It's just a little somethin'.

03:32.213 --> 03:33.178
Stop.

03:33.214 --> 03:34.546
Is this my apartment?

03:34.582 --> 03:35.347
I mean, yeah.

03:35.382 --> 03:36.582
You say you're never there,

03:36.617 --> 03:38.584
so I thought you could leave it
at your desk.

03:38.619 --> 03:39.451
You're amazing.

03:39.486 --> 03:40.252
I love it.

03:40.287 --> 03:41.653
[laughs]

03:41.689 --> 03:45.457
Merry Christmas.

03:45.492 --> 03:48.594
I would like mine in this,
please.

04:31.772 --> 04:35.407
[phone vibrates]

04:35.476 --> 04:36.174
Hi, Dad.

04:36.210 --> 04:37.542
Yep.

04:37.611 --> 04:40.012
Yep, no, I'm literally walking
out the door right now.

04:40.080 --> 04:42.514
I've already packed the car.

04:42.549 --> 04:44.082
Yep, of course.

04:44.151 --> 04:45.384
I'll drive safe.

04:45.419 --> 04:46.885
Dad, gotta get off the phone
to get in the car.

04:46.954 --> 04:48.353
Bye.

05:01.568 --> 05:03.201
Mrs. Miller, I know
the holidays are slow,

05:03.237 --> 05:06.938
but we should be able to find
you a tenant before New Year.

05:06.974 --> 05:07.806
Yep.

05:07.875 --> 05:08.473
[laughs]

05:08.542 --> 05:09.875
No, I...

05:09.910 --> 05:11.810
I can't tell you where I'm gonna
be moving the snowman.

05:11.845 --> 05:13.945
It... that would be cheating.

05:13.981 --> 05:15.814
Happy Holidays.

05:15.883 --> 05:16.715
Hey, bud.

05:16.750 --> 05:17.382
Hey buddy.

05:17.418 --> 05:18.717
Uh, I know you're busy.

05:18.752 --> 05:19.885
I just want to let you know
I'm still working on

05:19.920 --> 05:21.553
getting you that interview.

05:21.622 --> 05:24.156
You do realize this is poaching,
don't you?

05:24.224 --> 05:27.292
Oh, I'm sorry, I was just,
uh...

05:27.361 --> 05:28.860
My mom's kidding,
Josh.

05:28.896 --> 05:29.795
[laughs]

05:29.830 --> 05:30.696
Of course.

05:30.731 --> 05:32.497
Merry Christmas,
Mrs. Phillips.

05:32.566 --> 05:33.899
You're not five anymore,
Josh.

05:33.934 --> 05:35.367
You can call me Judy.

05:35.402 --> 05:38.970
And, it's not poaching if I'm
the one asking.

05:39.006 --> 05:41.506
I just wish your agency wasn't
all the way in London.

05:41.575 --> 05:43.408
IF I get the job.

05:43.444 --> 05:45.377
I'll try and set something up
before Christmas.

05:45.412 --> 05:47.079
You're the best.

05:47.147 --> 05:48.480
Yes, I am.

05:48.515 --> 05:49.514
I'll see you tomorrow night,
buddy.

05:49.583 --> 05:50.315
All right.

05:50.351 --> 05:51.950
Bye.

05:53.520 --> 05:56.054
So, you really want to move?

05:56.123 --> 05:58.790
I just wish we had more exciting
work for you.

05:58.826 --> 05:59.991
I love it here, Mom.

06:00.060 --> 06:01.226
That's not the issue.

06:01.261 --> 06:04.029
It's just, everything
that happened with Beth.

06:04.064 --> 06:06.465
I dunno, I think change
could be good.

06:06.500 --> 06:07.999
We just want you
to be happy.

06:08.068 --> 06:08.800
Me?

06:08.836 --> 06:10.102
I am happy.

06:10.137 --> 06:11.036
I'm very happy.

06:11.071 --> 06:11.737
Look.

06:11.772 --> 06:12.571
Look at this smile.

06:12.606 --> 06:13.705
This is a happy smile.

06:13.741 --> 06:15.140
Very happy.

06:16.110 --> 06:18.110
Hey, we need you to get
over there as soon as you can.

06:18.145 --> 06:19.878
Uh, okay.

06:19.913 --> 06:21.513
Where am I going?

06:21.548 --> 06:23.982
A leak at the River Street
rental.

06:24.017 --> 06:25.751
And, since they're
family friends...

06:25.786 --> 06:27.786
You are Mr. Fix It.

06:27.821 --> 06:29.121
[laughs]

06:29.189 --> 06:31.256
I don't know about all that,
but I can take a look.

06:31.291 --> 06:32.224
Okay, great.

06:32.292 --> 06:33.291
And, uh, while you're there,

06:33.327 --> 06:36.628
see if you can ask Lee
about his plans.

06:36.697 --> 06:40.232
Uh, what they're gonna do with
the house after the wedding?

06:40.300 --> 06:41.666
I left them a message.

06:41.702 --> 06:42.501
Okay.

06:42.536 --> 06:43.935
I got this.

06:49.476 --> 06:56.515
♪

07:24.011 --> 07:25.010
[tires squeal]

07:31.418 --> 07:34.619
Oh, shoot.

07:50.637 --> 07:52.337
I am so sorry.

07:52.372 --> 07:53.438
I... I was turning around,

07:53.474 --> 07:54.306
I didn't expect to see
anyone coming.

07:54.341 --> 07:55.240
To my driveway?

07:55.275 --> 07:57.108
Well, at the exact same...

07:57.144 --> 07:58.009
Sam?

07:58.045 --> 07:59.244
Mike?

07:59.313 --> 08:00.612
[laughs]

08:00.647 --> 08:01.646
Hi.

08:01.682 --> 08:03.315
Wow, it's...it's been a...

08:03.350 --> 08:04.583
...A long time.

08:04.618 --> 08:05.217
[laughs]

08:05.252 --> 08:06.418
Dad.

08:06.453 --> 08:07.219
Honey.

08:07.254 --> 08:08.553
So good to see you.

08:08.589 --> 08:10.188
Good to see you.

08:11.325 --> 08:12.257
You're the handyman?

08:12.292 --> 08:14.459
I am today.

08:14.528 --> 08:15.260
[laughs]

08:15.295 --> 08:16.161
Well, grab your tools.

08:16.196 --> 08:17.963
Let's get at it.

08:17.998 --> 08:19.831
Honey, how was your drive?

08:19.867 --> 08:20.765
It's good.

08:20.801 --> 08:21.633
Yeah?

08:21.668 --> 08:24.002
Yeah, it's so different here.

08:24.037 --> 08:25.270
I noticed the drip this morning.

08:25.339 --> 08:27.038
It's not good.

08:27.074 --> 08:28.673
Ooh.

08:28.709 --> 08:31.743
Yeah, okay, all right, well,
I'm on it.

08:31.778 --> 08:34.746
I just need to get up
into your attic.

08:34.815 --> 08:35.313
Okay.

08:35.349 --> 08:36.848
Thanks, Mike.

08:40.420 --> 08:42.721
Now, how long have you
known Mike?

08:42.756 --> 08:44.623
Uh, you know, I don't even
remember when we met,

08:44.658 --> 08:45.790
we were so young.

08:45.826 --> 08:46.691
Oh, no.

08:46.760 --> 08:47.826
They were inseparable
as kids.

08:47.895 --> 08:50.028
Yeah, for the summers
when we came here.

08:50.063 --> 08:52.898
Yeah, but, I mean, best friends
with school kid crushes,

08:52.966 --> 08:54.165
it was...

08:54.201 --> 08:55.767
[uncomfortably]
Oh Dad, that's a long time ago.

08:55.802 --> 08:58.303
It's nice to see you two
together again.

08:58.372 --> 08:59.771
Okay, you know what,

08:59.840 --> 09:00.906
I think you've talked your way
outta getting your treats.

09:00.941 --> 09:01.540
No.

09:01.575 --> 09:02.307
No.

09:02.342 --> 09:03.608
[laughs]

09:03.644 --> 09:05.911
Is that something that you
requested from the city?

09:05.946 --> 09:07.546
Honey, we've been here
for two weeks.

09:07.581 --> 09:08.413
Mm-hmm.

09:08.448 --> 09:09.414
Two weeks and loving it,
yeah.

09:09.449 --> 09:10.916
Uh-huh.

09:10.984 --> 09:13.318
But nothing beats Boston coffee
and did you get the holiday...

09:13.353 --> 09:14.419
Ah, yes.

09:14.454 --> 09:15.720
Good girl.

09:15.756 --> 09:17.622
Uh, now I know that you
were born and raised here,

09:17.691 --> 09:20.158
so you probably have all
your own holiday chocolates

09:20.193 --> 09:25.063
all lined up, but this is from
our favourite local store.

09:25.098 --> 09:26.431
It's not too sweet,
it's not too minty,

09:26.500 --> 09:27.766
and I figured it would help
you push through that

09:27.834 --> 09:29.801
final little wedding planning.

09:29.836 --> 09:30.969
[laughs]

09:31.004 --> 09:33.138
Peppermint bark
is my favourite.

09:33.206 --> 09:34.706
I kid you not.

09:34.741 --> 09:35.340
I love this.

09:35.375 --> 09:36.474
Thank you so much.

09:36.510 --> 09:37.509
Yay.

09:37.544 --> 09:38.209
What else do we got?

09:38.278 --> 09:39.644
What other treats?

09:57.998 --> 10:00.198
I can't believe you made this.

10:00.233 --> 10:03.034
Oh, I used to make 'em every
year with my art students.

10:03.070 --> 10:04.336
Even though I'm retired,

10:04.371 --> 10:06.738
I figured I would just keep
the tradition going.

10:06.773 --> 10:08.373
And since this is our
first Christmas together,

10:08.408 --> 10:10.041
I thought that it was
the perfect Christmas slash...

10:10.077 --> 10:12.177
... slash Wedding gift, right?

10:12.212 --> 10:13.378
Perfect.

10:13.413 --> 10:14.312
And there's chocolates
in every one of 'em.

10:14.348 --> 10:16.147
Oh, cute.

10:17.484 --> 10:18.783
Ah. I'll get out of your
guys' hair.

10:18.852 --> 10:20.986
But, uh, looks good up there.

10:21.021 --> 10:24.422
If you have any more leaks,
just give us a call.

10:24.458 --> 10:25.957
I definitely will.

10:25.993 --> 10:28.226
And, uh, tell your dad
that I'll call him another time

10:28.261 --> 10:29.694
about the house stuff, okay?

10:29.730 --> 10:30.362
Will do.

10:30.397 --> 10:31.196
Okay.

10:31.231 --> 10:32.130
All right, good to see ya.

10:32.165 --> 10:33.498
You too.

10:33.567 --> 10:36.868
Uh, I'll see you guys
all at the wedding.

10:36.903 --> 10:38.637
Hey.

10:38.672 --> 10:39.404
Good to see you.

10:39.473 --> 10:40.939
Yeah, you too.

10:40.974 --> 10:43.875
I mean, except for the near
collision outside, but...

10:43.910 --> 10:45.377
Yeah, well, hey.

10:45.412 --> 10:46.444
You never were a very
good driver.

10:46.513 --> 10:47.846
Hey.

10:47.881 --> 10:50.782
I was learning, and I was being
responsibly cautious.

10:50.817 --> 10:52.117
Oh, yeah.

10:52.152 --> 10:54.586
15 miles an hour, rocking out
to Sarah McLachlan?

10:54.621 --> 10:56.187
You can't speed to Sarah.

10:56.223 --> 10:57.022
Nah?

10:57.057 --> 10:59.457
Okay.

10:59.493 --> 11:01.426
Well, I know you're going to be
busy this week,

11:01.461 --> 11:04.396
but if you need a Christmas
in the Cape tour guide,

11:04.431 --> 11:05.697
let me know.

11:05.732 --> 11:07.866
Oh, thanks. Yeah.

11:07.934 --> 11:10.135
But you're gonna be busy
with your family and your wife,

11:10.170 --> 11:11.436
and all that.

11:11.471 --> 11:14.172
I'm, uh, yeah, I'm not
married anymore.

11:14.207 --> 11:15.540
What?

11:15.609 --> 11:17.609
I guess I... I figured
you woulda heard.

11:17.644 --> 11:19.611
No...no, I didn't...
I didn't hear that.

11:19.646 --> 11:20.445
I'm so sorry.

11:20.480 --> 11:21.513
It's all good.

11:21.548 --> 11:22.881
Really is.

11:22.916 --> 11:25.684
And, I wanted to say
I'm sorry too.

11:25.752 --> 11:27.318
Oh, for what?

11:27.387 --> 11:28.887
That summer.

11:28.922 --> 11:30.689
Your mom got sick.

11:30.724 --> 11:31.556
I really meant to...

11:31.591 --> 11:32.657
[shortly] Thank you.

11:32.693 --> 11:34.926
But we don't need
to talk about that.

11:34.961 --> 11:35.627
Okay.

11:35.662 --> 11:37.429
'Kay.

11:37.464 --> 11:38.463
Merry Christmas.

11:38.532 --> 11:40.365
Merry Christmas.

11:48.542 --> 11:49.541
It took four people-

11:49.576 --> 11:50.208
Four-

11:50.243 --> 11:51.142
to get the tree in.

11:51.178 --> 11:52.977
Okay, how big is your tree?

11:53.013 --> 11:56.114
And, we actually had
to cut a foot of it off

11:56.183 --> 11:57.515
to even get it in.

11:57.551 --> 11:58.983
[laughs]

11:59.019 --> 12:00.452
I've always been a sucker
for the most ridiculously large

12:00.487 --> 12:01.953
Christmas trees.

12:01.988 --> 12:03.321
And holiday weddings.

12:03.390 --> 12:04.856
Well, okay, I will admit it.

12:04.891 --> 12:06.257
I'm a little Christmas crazy.

12:06.326 --> 12:08.059
It's a Christmas Eve wedding.

12:08.128 --> 12:08.660
Mm-hmm.

12:08.695 --> 12:10.361
Exactly.

12:10.430 --> 12:13.231
With our closest friends
and family.

12:13.266 --> 12:16.334
It's just my absolute
favourite time of the year.

12:16.369 --> 12:20.305
It always makes me feel like
I'm part of something bigger.

12:20.340 --> 12:23.541
So, it's an unconventional day
for a wedding, but...

12:23.577 --> 12:26.344
But perfect for us.

12:26.379 --> 12:29.347
It is.

12:29.416 --> 12:35.286
And finding this love now is
my own Christmas miracle.

12:35.322 --> 12:37.489
Mine too.

12:38.725 --> 12:40.725
[clears throat]

12:40.761 --> 12:41.826
Well, I got that
tree decorated,

12:41.862 --> 12:43.461
and I'd love for you
to come see it.

12:43.497 --> 12:44.629
So, do you want to come
by the house,

12:44.664 --> 12:46.131
and we can make some cookies,

12:46.166 --> 12:48.266
or finish making the chocolate
moulds for the wedding favours?

12:48.301 --> 12:49.434
Yeah, but not tomorrow.

12:49.469 --> 12:50.502
Oh, no.

12:50.537 --> 12:52.036
Oh, why, what's tomorrow?

12:52.072 --> 12:54.172
We're going to get
your Christmas tree.

12:54.207 --> 12:56.274
We wanted you here
to get the tree.

12:56.309 --> 12:58.743
Oh, yeah.

12:58.779 --> 13:01.513
And we have to swing by the
hotel and finish some details

13:01.548 --> 13:04.149
with the wedding coordinator.

13:04.184 --> 13:06.050
You don't have to go if you
think it's gonna be boring.

13:06.086 --> 13:07.385
I mean, you could always check
out the town.

13:07.420 --> 13:09.154
It's a lot different
at Christmas

13:09.189 --> 13:10.121
than what you're used to.

13:10.157 --> 13:11.656
Thank you.

13:11.691 --> 13:13.391
Well, I have some very special
Christmas bark

13:13.426 --> 13:15.260
that I'd like to share.

13:15.295 --> 13:16.561
May I interest you?

13:16.596 --> 13:17.262
Ahh, Christmas bark.

13:17.330 --> 13:18.296
Yes.

13:18.331 --> 13:19.230
I'm gonna need some
extra energy,

13:19.299 --> 13:20.465
'cause I'm walking you home.

13:20.500 --> 13:21.733
Oh, like you need an excuse.

13:21.768 --> 13:23.535
[laughs]

13:23.570 --> 13:24.068
Cheers.

13:24.104 --> 13:25.036
Cheers.

13:25.071 --> 13:26.004
Cheers, Merry Christmas.

13:26.039 --> 13:26.871
Oh!

13:26.907 --> 13:28.306
[laughs]

13:58.905 --> 14:02.040
First family photo
we ever put up.

14:02.075 --> 14:04.943
It's a good one.

14:04.978 --> 14:06.277
Yeah.

14:06.313 --> 14:09.080
She was really talented,
wasn't she?

14:09.115 --> 14:14.285
Well, like I always say,
you guys are a lot alike.

14:14.321 --> 14:19.190
Oh... You still wear
your mom's necklace.

14:19.226 --> 14:21.025
What is it she always
used to say?

14:21.061 --> 14:22.493
Um...

14:22.529 --> 14:25.964
"Look up at the stars and..."

14:26.032 --> 14:27.732
"Know that I'll always
be there."

14:27.767 --> 14:30.335
Yeah.

14:30.370 --> 14:34.906
I never take it off.

14:34.941 --> 14:36.107
[sighs]

14:36.176 --> 14:38.042
[clears throat]

14:38.078 --> 14:41.746
You know, I just wanna
thank you.

14:41.781 --> 14:44.582
You know, for all your support
with this.

14:44.618 --> 14:45.850
Means a lot to me.

14:45.886 --> 14:49.287
Oh, Dad. I just want you
to be happy.

14:49.322 --> 14:51.389
You know that.

14:51.424 --> 14:54.158
And I really like Helen.

14:54.194 --> 14:58.596
I'm excited for you to get
to know her better.

14:58.632 --> 15:03.835
I know it's only been 10 months,
but once we move in together.

15:03.870 --> 15:06.170
Is that what you and Mike
were talking about earlier,

15:06.206 --> 15:08.640
about what to do
with the house?

15:08.675 --> 15:11.175
Well, they just kinda need
to know if,

15:11.211 --> 15:14.045
uh, I'm gonna continue
to rent

15:14.080 --> 15:19.884
after I move in with Helen,
or... sell.

15:19.920 --> 15:21.052
Is that what you wanna do?

15:21.087 --> 15:24.188
Do you... do you wanna sell it?

15:24.224 --> 15:28.059
Well, I think it's something we
both need to decide, right?

15:28.094 --> 15:29.360
I don't think so.

15:29.396 --> 15:30.261
I mean, I haven't been here
in so many years.

15:30.330 --> 15:31.062
I don't...

15:31.097 --> 15:32.397
Hey. Hey. You know what?

15:32.465 --> 15:34.799
We... we don't have to talk
about this right now.

15:34.834 --> 15:38.069
We have lots of time.

15:38.104 --> 15:39.570
Okay?

15:39.606 --> 15:40.405
Thanks.

15:40.473 --> 15:41.205
'Kay.

15:41.241 --> 15:42.640
Hmm.

15:42.676 --> 15:44.876
Want more tea?

15:44.911 --> 15:47.211
You know what, I think,
I um, I'm beat.

15:47.247 --> 15:48.980
I think I'm gonna go to bed.

15:49.015 --> 15:50.615
Okay, honey.

15:50.650 --> 15:53.084
Okay.

15:53.119 --> 15:54.118
I love you.

15:54.154 --> 15:55.753
I love you too, babe.

15:57.590 --> 15:59.390
[sighs]

16:22.949 --> 16:24.015
Jasper, hi.

16:24.050 --> 16:25.216
Uh, I was actually going
to call you,

16:25.285 --> 16:26.217
to see if there are any...

16:26.286 --> 16:27.251
Updates?

16:27.287 --> 16:28.252
Well, there are.

16:28.288 --> 16:29.487
<i> Good.</i>

16:29.556 --> 16:30.955
Great.

16:31.024 --> 16:33.524
As I suspected, our chief editor
loves your photos, but...

16:33.560 --> 16:35.760
She also loves three
other submissions.

16:35.795 --> 16:38.463
There are three other people
in the running still?

16:38.531 --> 16:39.897
<i> Unfortunately, there was</i>
<i> no clear-cut decision</i>

16:39.933 --> 16:41.265
<i> on who should get it,</i>

16:41.334 --> 16:43.968
so we're giving all four of you
the chance to resubmit.

16:44.004 --> 16:46.104
<i> Same title and concept, but...</i>

16:46.139 --> 16:48.539
Uh, I'm not in Boston,
I'm on the Cape.

16:48.575 --> 16:49.774
<i> Well, that's okay.</i>

16:49.843 --> 16:51.743
<i> It's the feeling of</i>
<i> Christmas we're after.</i>

16:51.811 --> 16:54.912
And everyone loves
Cape Cod, so...

16:54.948 --> 16:57.682
<i> You have until midnight on</i>
<i> December 23rd to turn it in.</i>

16:57.717 --> 16:59.417
<i> I know it's a bit of a rush,</i>
<i> but...</i>

16:59.486 --> 17:02.086
Is it still for the staff
position, too?

17:02.122 --> 17:03.788
It is, and editor's quirk,

17:03.823 --> 17:06.190
she wants to give someone
a gift on Christmas.

17:06.226 --> 17:08.993
So, that's when we'll reveal
which one of you we select.

17:10.330 --> 17:13.431
Wow. That's, um...

17:13.466 --> 17:14.732
Wow.

17:14.768 --> 17:16.000
Just remember: Christmas.

17:16.036 --> 17:18.469
Something we haven't seen.

17:18.505 --> 17:20.438
<i> Good luck.</i>

17:20.473 --> 17:22.006
Thank you.

17:24.878 --> 17:26.177
All right.

17:28.948 --> 17:31.482
Christmas.

17:31.551 --> 17:33.684
Here.

17:35.488 --> 17:38.856
♪

17:38.925 --> 17:39.891
Hmm.

17:45.999 --> 17:46.998
Whoo!

17:48.935 --> 17:50.435
Hi.

17:50.470 --> 17:52.003
Uh, hi.

17:52.038 --> 17:54.072
Um, I'm sorry to barge
in like that.

17:54.107 --> 17:59.043
Uh, I'm wondering if that tour
guide offer is still available.

18:08.788 --> 18:09.854
I know it's a bit of
an odd req

18:09.923 --> 18:12.356
It's just, uh, Boston,
I know.

18:12.392 --> 18:14.659
But I have not been here
since I was 17,

18:14.694 --> 18:16.160
and they've only given me
three days to do it,

18:16.196 --> 18:18.262
and normally I'd take, like,
a week to scout, and plan...

18:18.298 --> 18:19.597
Take this.
It'll help.

18:19.632 --> 18:20.331
Thank you.

18:20.400 --> 18:21.566
All right.

18:23.570 --> 18:27.738
Okay. I'm sorry, uh, it's...
I thought I was done.

18:27.774 --> 18:28.306
You know?

18:28.341 --> 18:28.973
And now...

18:29.042 --> 18:30.475
You're starting over.

18:30.543 --> 18:31.576
But it's a really
good opportunity.

18:31.611 --> 18:32.410
Yeah.

18:32.479 --> 18:33.544
It's just at a really bad time.

18:33.580 --> 18:35.680
And, it's doable though,
right?

18:35.748 --> 18:36.647
I, yeah...

18:36.683 --> 18:38.249
Yeah.

18:38.284 --> 18:38.783
Wanna sit?

18:38.818 --> 18:39.550
Sure, yeah.

18:39.586 --> 18:41.519
Okay.

18:42.822 --> 18:45.656
You're saying you want to go see
the old lighthouse?

18:45.692 --> 18:48.292
I know it's restricted, but
I thought maybe you know

18:48.361 --> 18:50.328
somebody that could get me in?

18:50.363 --> 18:51.295
Yeah, I might.

18:51.331 --> 18:52.330
Really?

18:52.365 --> 18:53.531
I mean, I don't know
if it's right.

18:53.600 --> 18:54.765
I just, it was the first place
I thought of,

18:54.801 --> 18:56.367
so I figured I should at least
check it out.

18:56.402 --> 18:58.369
Yeah, I mean, there are some
pretty amazing views out there.

18:58.404 --> 19:01.105
I need amazing
right about now.

19:01.141 --> 19:01.706
All right, then.

19:01.774 --> 19:03.007
In my opinion,

19:03.076 --> 19:05.476
you're in the perfect place
for this assignment.

19:05.545 --> 19:07.278
Is that the tour guide talking?

19:07.347 --> 19:08.312
<i> Tour guide voice.</i>

19:08.348 --> 19:09.280
[laughs]

19:09.315 --> 19:10.114
Yeah.

19:10.150 --> 19:11.582
So, uh, 3:30?

19:11.618 --> 19:12.750
I'll take it.

19:12.785 --> 19:13.251
Okay.

19:13.286 --> 19:13.818
I love it.

19:13.887 --> 19:14.752
All right.

19:14.787 --> 19:16.087
It... it's uh...

19:17.323 --> 19:18.222
there you go.

19:18.291 --> 19:19.157
Thank you.

19:19.192 --> 19:19.957
Cheers.

19:19.993 --> 19:20.791
Oh.

19:20.827 --> 19:24.495
You know.

19:24.531 --> 19:26.130
[awkwardly]
Bye.

19:32.705 --> 19:44.549
<i> [upbeat instrumental music]</i>
<i> ♪</i>

19:44.584 --> 19:49.153
<i> [instrumental music</i>
<i> becomes melancholy]</i>
<i> ♪</i>

20:00.700 --> 20:03.067
Want one more?
Here, I'll break it off.

20:03.102 --> 20:03.868
Ah, I can't get it.

20:03.937 --> 20:04.635
Here.

20:04.671 --> 20:06.070
[laughs]

20:06.105 --> 20:06.704
<i> I got it.</i>

20:06.739 --> 20:07.471
-Hi.
-Hi.

20:07.540 --> 20:08.573
<i> Hey.</i>

20:08.608 --> 20:10.141
You ready to go find
the perfect tree?

20:10.176 --> 20:11.709
Yeah.

20:20.520 --> 20:21.586
Oh, come on.

20:21.621 --> 20:22.820
[grunts]

20:22.855 --> 20:23.487
Okay.

20:23.556 --> 20:24.155
How's that?

20:24.224 --> 20:25.957
Is that straighter?

20:26.025 --> 20:27.525
[both women hum disapprovingly]

20:27.560 --> 20:29.327
Oh, that's... doesn't
sound good.

20:29.362 --> 20:31.362
Uh, well, no, I think it's just

20:31.431 --> 20:32.830
the nature of the tree
actually, Dad.

20:32.899 --> 20:34.932
I think it looks... good.

20:34.968 --> 20:38.636
It's... what I got for ya.

20:38.671 --> 20:41.005
Move over just a little bit,
honey.

20:41.074 --> 20:45.243
Okay, it's... it's...
it's fine.

20:46.379 --> 20:48.813
Helen, I can't believe you make
your own ornaments.

20:48.848 --> 20:49.847
Oh, these?

20:49.916 --> 20:52.183
Well, feel free to use 'em,
or not.

20:52.218 --> 20:54.919
I just had so many extra ones
from my house that I picked out

20:54.988 --> 20:57.355
a few special ones
from each year,

20:57.423 --> 20:58.656
and brought 'em over here.

20:58.725 --> 21:00.224
[chuckles]

21:00.260 --> 21:01.993
It sounds like so much work.

21:02.028 --> 21:03.194
Huh.

21:03.229 --> 21:04.629
No, I've been doing it
since I was little.

21:04.664 --> 21:06.797
It just brings me
so much joy.

21:06.833 --> 21:08.699
Plus, every single one of them
is unique.

21:08.735 --> 21:09.867
Mm-hmm.

21:09.902 --> 21:15.406
Each one tells its very own
special story.

21:15.441 --> 21:18.109
Maybe we could make some?

21:18.144 --> 21:19.110
Of course we can.

21:19.178 --> 21:20.244
Start our own tradition.

21:20.280 --> 21:21.545
Yeah.

21:21.581 --> 21:23.314
Just, maybe later,

21:23.349 --> 21:24.982
'cause Mike's coming
to get me soon.

21:25.018 --> 21:27.084
<i> Oh, yeah, yeah, yeah.</i>

21:27.120 --> 21:28.352
[sighs]

21:28.388 --> 21:31.455
Guys, I'm so sorry I have to do
this work stuff.

21:31.491 --> 21:32.990
Oh, honey, no.
That's okay.

21:33.026 --> 21:36.127
I know that's not how you want
to spend your holiday, but...

21:36.195 --> 21:39.063
well, just go have fun.

21:39.132 --> 21:40.331
I'll try.

21:40.366 --> 21:41.332
[exhales]

21:42.568 --> 21:45.836
Sorry, I gotta, I gotta
straighten this tree.

21:45.872 --> 21:47.038
It's not working.

21:47.073 --> 21:48.973
It's not working for me.

22:00.119 --> 22:05.189
You ready to be inspired?

22:05.224 --> 22:08.959
Do you remember the picture
my mom took of us up here?

22:08.995 --> 22:10.161
[laughs]

22:10.229 --> 22:11.195
[camera shutter snaps]

22:11.230 --> 22:12.363
Oh, we were so proud
of ourselves.

22:12.398 --> 22:13.831
Yeah, as we should be.

22:13.866 --> 22:14.832
A lot of stairs in there.

22:14.867 --> 22:15.666
Yeah.

22:15.702 --> 22:17.168
You beat me to the top.

22:17.203 --> 22:18.102
I did, really?

22:18.137 --> 22:19.103
Oh yeah.

22:19.138 --> 22:21.072
Yeah, I chased you
the whole way.

22:23.242 --> 22:24.241
Well...

22:24.310 --> 22:25.776
[camera shutter snaps]

22:25.812 --> 22:29.146
She kept that picture on our
mantle for... a lot of years.

22:29.215 --> 22:32.016
She did like me.

22:32.051 --> 22:33.818
Yeah.

22:33.853 --> 22:35.653
She did.

22:42.328 --> 22:45.763
Oh, they don't keep the key
under the rock anymore.

22:45.798 --> 22:50.201
Surprisingly, they actually
trust me with it.

22:50.236 --> 22:51.202
After you.

22:51.237 --> 22:52.703
Thank you.

23:00.446 --> 23:01.779
It's so cozy here.

23:02.315 --> 23:03.414
Yeah.

23:10.456 --> 23:12.123
Whoo!

23:12.158 --> 23:14.759
Yeah, these stairs have gotten
steeper, huh?

23:17.563 --> 23:19.296
All right.

23:26.973 --> 23:27.671
Okay.

23:27.707 --> 23:29.840
So, what do you think?

23:29.876 --> 23:31.442
<i> I mean, it's a little different</i>
<i> in winter,</i>

23:31.477 --> 23:34.478
<i> but... it's usually a great</i>
<i> view up here.</i>

23:34.514 --> 23:36.947
<i> Shame about the fog.</i>

23:36.983 --> 23:37.848
If it weren't so remote,

23:37.917 --> 23:39.216
I'd bring the snowman out here.

23:39.252 --> 23:40.751
The... what?

23:40.787 --> 23:42.653
What are you talking about?

23:42.688 --> 23:43.988
Magic?

23:44.023 --> 23:45.656
Magic?

23:45.691 --> 23:47.091
You really don't know about
the magic snowman?

23:47.126 --> 23:48.559
I don't, no.

23:48.594 --> 23:50.428
Oh.

23:50.496 --> 23:54.832
So, every night, for as long as
I can remember,

23:54.867 --> 23:59.270
someone moves a giant snowman
somewhere in town,

23:59.338 --> 24:01.372
for the week leading up
to Christmas.

24:01.407 --> 24:04.742
And, why would someone
do that?

24:04.777 --> 24:07.445
So that some lucky kids can find
a magic snowman,

24:07.513 --> 24:10.514
ring the bell that he's holding,
and make a wish?

24:10.550 --> 24:15.152
And is that somebody... you?

24:15.221 --> 24:17.488
Last five years, yeah.

24:17.523 --> 24:19.857
Pretty adorable.

24:19.892 --> 24:21.459
So, what do you think?

24:21.494 --> 24:23.694
Well, I was hoping to get
the Christmas lights over

24:23.729 --> 24:27.097
on the hillside, but, um...
I mean, with this fog,

24:27.133 --> 24:28.499
I don't think I can.

24:28.534 --> 24:30.468
Hmm.

24:30.503 --> 24:33.103
I just think we're too far out.

24:33.139 --> 24:34.238
Yeah.

24:34.273 --> 24:37.508
I guess it's a good thing
you know me.

24:37.543 --> 24:39.910
Now, what are you
talking about?

24:39.946 --> 24:41.579
Well, I wouldn't be much
of a tour guide

24:41.614 --> 24:43.981
if I only took you to one place,
right?

24:44.016 --> 24:46.617
And, we're too far out, so...

24:46.652 --> 24:48.652
So?...

24:48.688 --> 24:54.692
So maybe we just need to get
a little closer to Christmas.

24:57.530 --> 25:06.003
<i> [instrumental Christmas musi</i>

25:06.038 --> 25:07.605
So you have to throw a Christmas
party every year

25:07.640 --> 25:08.973
for the Chamber of Commerce?

25:09.008 --> 25:11.342
Well, I...I volunteer to help
every year,

25:11.377 --> 25:13.878
and securing a house
for the Christmas party's

25:13.913 --> 25:14.945
just a part of it.

25:14.981 --> 25:16.347
They work really hard
for the town,

25:16.415 --> 25:20.451
so it's nice that tonight
they just get to celebrate.

25:20.520 --> 25:23.521
Well, this seems like
the perfect place for it.

25:23.556 --> 25:24.388
[laughs]

25:24.457 --> 25:26.790
You haven't seen nothing yet.

25:26.826 --> 25:30.494
Now this is Christmas
on the Cape.

25:30.530 --> 25:33.497
This is amazing.

25:33.533 --> 25:34.665
Yeah.

25:34.700 --> 25:38.435
Well, you said you kinda needed
it, so...

25:38.504 --> 25:39.336
Wow.

25:39.372 --> 25:40.037
Yeah.

25:40.072 --> 25:40.871
There you are.

25:40.907 --> 25:42.172
Hey.

25:42.208 --> 25:43.207
Hey, I was wondering when
you were gonna show up.

25:43.242 --> 25:44.575
You're usually one of the first.

25:44.610 --> 25:46.143
Ah, yeah, sorry about that.

25:46.212 --> 25:47.878
I was just helping Sam.

25:47.914 --> 25:50.381
Josh, you... you remember Sam,
right?

25:50.449 --> 25:52.850
We never met, but he talked
about you a lot.

25:52.919 --> 25:53.817
Did he?

25:53.886 --> 25:55.085
<i> Yes, he did.</i>

25:55.121 --> 25:56.020
Uh...

25:56.055 --> 25:56.887
[clears throat]

25:56.923 --> 25:59.189
Not a lot.

25:59.225 --> 26:01.525
Uh, this is my wife, Hannah.

26:01.594 --> 26:02.092
Hi.

26:02.128 --> 26:03.794
Hey, Hannah.

26:03.863 --> 26:04.795
I'm Sam.

26:04.864 --> 26:05.396
-Hi Sam.
-So nice to meet you.

26:05.431 --> 26:07.131
You too.

26:07.166 --> 26:08.232
Officially.

26:08.301 --> 26:10.000
Okay, I promised that, uh,

26:10.036 --> 26:11.402
I'd find the biscuits
for my lovely wife, so...

26:11.437 --> 26:14.271
That's uh, that's British
for "cookies."

26:14.340 --> 26:15.039
We've got cookies.

26:15.074 --> 26:16.540
See?

26:16.576 --> 26:18.609
You're already ready
for your move to London.

26:18.644 --> 26:20.110
Oh, and I just want to let
you know, my ...uh,

26:20.146 --> 26:21.779
boss's assistant will be giving
you a call to set up

26:21.814 --> 26:23.714
that interview, so keep
your phone close.

26:23.749 --> 26:24.582
All right.

26:24.650 --> 26:25.649
Thanks buddy, I appreciate it.

26:25.685 --> 26:27.651
-Merry Christmas.
-Merry Christmas.

26:30.423 --> 26:33.157
You're moving to London?

26:33.192 --> 26:35.626
Yeah, well, I mean, it wouldn't
be till the new year,

26:35.661 --> 26:37.127
if I even get the job.

26:37.163 --> 26:39.897
But, uh, he works for a pretty
big commercial leasing company.

26:39.932 --> 26:43.834
They handle a lot of the high
rises in central London.

26:43.869 --> 26:46.136
Sounds exciting.

26:46.172 --> 26:49.373
No, I just... I don't know,

26:49.408 --> 26:52.876
I can't picture you anywhere
else but here.

26:52.945 --> 26:55.245
I guess I was just looking
for something new,

26:55.281 --> 26:56.113
you know?

26:56.148 --> 26:57.681
Fresh start.

26:57.717 --> 26:59.249
And busy's good.

26:59.318 --> 27:00.618
Yes.

27:00.653 --> 27:02.820
But hey, you, why don't you
check out the party,

27:02.855 --> 27:05.389
and I'm gonna gather up
the gifts for the toy drive.

27:05.424 --> 27:07.391
Toy... we're doing a toy drive?

27:07.426 --> 27:10.527
We're wrapping gifts that have
already been collected.

27:10.563 --> 27:12.796
It's sort of a tradition
at this party.

27:12.832 --> 27:14.732
People get real into it.

27:14.767 --> 27:15.866
Nice.

27:15.901 --> 27:17.234
But you, you gotta work, so go.
Go focus.

27:17.269 --> 27:19.670
Yeah, I mean I'm pretty good
at... at wrapping, so...

27:19.705 --> 27:21.672
All right.  Well, if you finish
early, you can jump in.

27:21.741 --> 27:23.273
How's that?

27:23.309 --> 27:24.208
Deal.

27:24.243 --> 27:25.576
See ya.

27:35.988 --> 27:39.556
[shutter snaps]

27:51.370 --> 28:01.178
♪

28:01.213 --> 28:09.019
♪

28:09.055 --> 28:12.723
[shutter snaps]

28:14.894 --> 28:16.360
<i> Everybody gather round.</i>

28:16.395 --> 28:18.595
<i> It's present wrapping time.</i>

28:25.705 --> 28:29.073
Okay, now I know that
this isn't a "competition."

28:29.141 --> 28:32.810
But, whoever wraps the most
gifts, all six sides covered,

28:32.845 --> 28:35.379
we know the rules,
may or may not go home

28:35.414 --> 28:40.117
with all of the leftover
cookies.

28:40.152 --> 28:41.452
Are all these gifts
for the kids?

28:41.487 --> 28:43.053
Yeah.

28:43.089 --> 28:45.589
It's a good thing I came
when I did.

28:45.658 --> 28:46.523
Done with your work already?

28:46.559 --> 28:48.459
No, but I'm ready to wrap.

28:48.494 --> 28:49.960
[laughs]

28:49.995 --> 28:51.695
All right.

28:51.731 --> 28:54.231
<i> [Jazzy version of</i>
<i> "The First Noel"]</i>
<i> ♪ The First Noel, ♪</i>

28:54.266 --> 28:58.268
<i> ♪ the Angel did say</i> ♪

28:58.304 --> 29:02.172
♪<i> Was to certain</i>
<i> poor shepherds</i> ♪

29:02.208 --> 29:06.343
♪<i> in fields where</i>
<i> they lay</i> ♪

29:06.378 --> 29:09.980
♪<i> In fields where</i>
<i> they lay</i> ♪

29:10.015 --> 29:13.884
♪<i> they keeping their sheep</i> ♪

29:13.953 --> 29:21.759
♪<i> On a cold winter's night</i>
<i> that was so deep</i> ♪

29:21.794 --> 29:29.566
♪<i> Noel, Noel, Noel, Noel</i> ♪

29:29.602 --> 29:31.135
I have to admit,

29:31.170 --> 29:33.670
I did not know the true value of
double-sided tape until tonight.

29:33.739 --> 29:36.707
Yeah, you uh, you wrapped
about a hundred presents in,

29:36.742 --> 29:37.741
what, ten minutes?

29:37.777 --> 29:39.543
It was for a good cause.

29:39.578 --> 29:40.844
And, you know what?

29:40.880 --> 29:42.613
If this whole photography career
doesn't pan out...

29:42.648 --> 29:45.082
[sighs]

29:45.117 --> 29:47.885
That's not gonna happen.

29:48.854 --> 29:50.387
You know what's funny?

29:50.422 --> 29:54.758
I grew up watching my mom take
all of these amazing photos.

29:54.794 --> 29:57.060
It was so inspiring.

29:57.096 --> 29:59.463
And then I always pictured
that I was going to be

29:59.498 --> 30:02.966
a freelance photographer
when I grew up.

30:03.035 --> 30:06.236
Well, it looks like you...
you nailed that.

30:06.272 --> 30:09.606
Yeah, you know what?
I just...

30:09.642 --> 30:12.242
I don't know
if I'm cut out for it.

30:12.278 --> 30:15.445
I feel like I should be doing
something more practical.

30:15.514 --> 30:17.247
And that's what this staff
position would be?

30:17.316 --> 30:18.949
It's a good opportunity.

30:18.984 --> 30:24.021
But to get it, I really need
to wow them.

30:24.056 --> 30:25.889
Okay.

30:25.958 --> 30:30.661
Like, I need to get
the first rays of dawn,

30:30.729 --> 30:33.897
against the last of
the Christmas lights.

30:33.933 --> 30:34.798
Mm-hmm.

30:34.834 --> 30:35.999
You know what, I...

30:36.035 --> 30:37.467
I just, I need to capture
that hope

30:37.503 --> 30:39.069
that only comes around
once a year.

30:39.104 --> 30:42.339
That's... that's what I need.

30:42.374 --> 30:46.977
Why don't we stay here and see
if you can capture it?

30:47.012 --> 30:49.780
I mean, we're here.

30:49.849 --> 30:50.981
Right?

30:51.016 --> 30:53.450
And if this is the view...

30:53.485 --> 30:55.485
I'm not gonna ask you to stay up
with me all night.

30:55.521 --> 30:56.787
Why not?

30:56.822 --> 30:58.555
Look, I'm the guy who's gotta
lock up, anyways.

30:58.591 --> 30:59.423
Oh, Mike.

30:59.491 --> 31:00.524
Why are you doing this?

31:00.559 --> 31:02.559
It's Christmas, isn't it?

31:02.628 --> 31:03.760
Right? And I like
to help people.

31:03.796 --> 31:04.595
I don't buy it.

31:04.630 --> 31:06.563
Why are you doing this?

31:06.599 --> 31:08.765
Okay, fine.

31:08.834 --> 31:11.435
I know you don't want to talk
about it.

31:11.470 --> 31:14.504
But I wasn't there for you
when I should have been.

31:14.540 --> 31:16.139
You didn't know what was
going on with my mom.

31:16.175 --> 31:18.709
It was...

31:18.744 --> 31:20.777
You know, it all happened
so fast.

31:20.813 --> 31:24.381
Still, I know that this is just
a small thing,

31:24.416 --> 31:28.952
but I'd really like to try
and be here for you now.

31:28.988 --> 31:30.187
Let's get you that shot.

31:30.256 --> 31:31.255
[giggles]

31:37.830 --> 31:38.962
[text alert]

31:45.004 --> 31:46.370
Yes, yeah, of course.

31:46.405 --> 31:48.906
And, uh, roger that.

31:48.941 --> 31:50.040
Is everything okay?

31:50.075 --> 31:51.375
As long as we're
out of here

31:51.410 --> 31:53.343
before the cleaning crew arrive,
we're good to go.

31:53.379 --> 31:54.344
You're amazing.

31:54.380 --> 31:55.345
[laughs]

31:55.381 --> 31:57.981
Just you wait.

31:58.817 --> 31:59.983
What is that?

32:00.019 --> 32:03.253
That is enough ammo
to keep a horse awake.

32:03.289 --> 32:04.721
Yeah.

32:05.291 --> 32:06.356
Yeah.

32:07.893 --> 32:09.526
Well, I guess we'll need it
if we're gonna stay up till...

32:09.561 --> 32:10.761
[sighs]
sunrise.

32:10.829 --> 32:14.331
Yeah, um... About that.

32:14.366 --> 32:17.634
Light isn't going to change
for a while, so...

32:17.703 --> 32:21.238
you wanna go see a snowman?

32:22.641 --> 32:23.974
[laughs]

32:29.415 --> 32:31.782
Uh, is he as heavy as he looks?

32:31.817 --> 32:32.449
No.

32:32.484 --> 32:33.283
I dunno.

32:33.319 --> 32:35.085
Then, yes.

32:35.120 --> 32:37.187
Gotta keep that magic alive,
right?

32:37.222 --> 32:38.588
[laughs]

32:38.657 --> 32:39.756
Yep.

32:39.825 --> 32:41.825
All right, so pick a side,
either side.

32:41.860 --> 32:42.759
Sure.

32:42.795 --> 32:44.494
Uh, you just...yeah,
reach in.

32:44.563 --> 32:45.162
Oh.

32:45.230 --> 32:46.596
[giggles]
Yep.

32:47.066 --> 32:49.032
Oh! Oh!!

32:49.068 --> 32:50.634
Great. Yeah, he is light.

32:50.669 --> 32:52.970
Awkward, but light.

32:53.005 --> 32:55.205
How do you think I move him
every night by myself?

32:55.240 --> 32:58.075
Oh, just thought it was
your superhuman strength.

32:58.143 --> 32:59.543
I should've gone with that.

33:00.813 --> 33:01.511
Okay.

33:01.580 --> 33:02.479
Okay, up, up, up.

33:02.548 --> 33:03.547
[groans]

33:03.582 --> 33:04.781
All right.

33:04.850 --> 33:07.017
Now let's just, uh, find
a good spot for him.

33:07.052 --> 33:07.718
[exhales]

33:07.786 --> 33:08.986
Find?

33:09.021 --> 33:11.755
I can't make it too easy
on the kids, right?

33:11.790 --> 33:12.789
[grunts]

33:12.858 --> 33:13.824
Okay.

33:19.098 --> 33:20.230
I don't know.

33:20.265 --> 33:22.199
A snowman in front of
an ice cream shop?

33:22.234 --> 33:23.500
Too cold.

33:23.535 --> 33:25.335
Yeah.

33:25.371 --> 33:27.137
Let's get him out of here.

33:30.576 --> 33:31.408
[strains]
Which way?

33:31.443 --> 33:33.810
Let's go that... no,
up...

33:33.846 --> 33:35.812
[exhales]

33:35.848 --> 33:38.248
I mean, it's cute,
but...

33:38.283 --> 33:40.217
Yeah, too obvious?

33:40.252 --> 33:41.985
Yeah.

33:42.021 --> 33:45.655
Well, get in there,
though.

33:45.691 --> 33:47.157
Okay.

33:49.128 --> 33:50.694
Perfect picture opportunity.

33:50.729 --> 33:51.695
Oh...

33:51.730 --> 33:54.598
I see how it is.

33:54.633 --> 33:57.367
Love at first snow.

34:00.372 --> 34:02.606
Finally, I think he's
actually good for tonight.

34:02.641 --> 34:04.307
Mm-hmm.

34:04.343 --> 34:06.510
I just can't believe you have
the keys to this place.

34:06.545 --> 34:12.816
Yeah, well... I kinda help
sponsor the kids' team.

34:12.885 --> 34:14.885
How will you ever leave this?

34:14.920 --> 34:16.586
You're practically the mayor
of this town.

34:16.655 --> 34:17.721
[laughs]

34:17.756 --> 34:19.356
I don't know about all that.

34:19.391 --> 34:20.991
Um, yeah, it'll be hard,

34:21.026 --> 34:24.194
but it can feel a little too
small sometimes, too.

34:24.229 --> 34:25.228
You know?

34:25.264 --> 34:29.332
Got a lot of memories.

34:29.368 --> 34:31.101
It's cold. Come on,
let's go.

34:31.136 --> 34:33.036
Here.

34:33.072 --> 34:36.940
Um... Does your ex-wife
still live here?

34:36.975 --> 34:38.141
No.

34:38.177 --> 34:41.044
No. She moved back to Ohio
after the divorce.

34:41.080 --> 34:44.147
It's all good, in the grand
scheme of things.

34:44.183 --> 34:46.516
Wow, you always do that,
don't you?

34:46.585 --> 34:47.851
Do what?

34:47.920 --> 34:49.686
Make light of things?

34:49.721 --> 34:52.222
I guess I'm just an upbeat
kinda guy.

34:52.257 --> 34:53.090
[chuckles]

34:53.125 --> 34:54.791
Yeah, you are.

34:54.827 --> 34:55.492
But...

34:55.527 --> 34:56.259
No, no, no.

34:56.295 --> 34:57.127
Look, it's fine.

34:57.162 --> 34:59.563
We were young,
you know?

34:59.598 --> 35:02.232
We grew apart,
wanted different things.

35:02.301 --> 35:06.069
I tried to adapt,
make her happy, but...

35:06.105 --> 35:08.872
end of the day, it just didn't
fix anything.

35:08.907 --> 35:10.841
Yeah, I just wish I had seen
it coming.

35:10.876 --> 35:12.375
Oh, you know what, you can't do
that to yourself.

35:12.444 --> 35:16.847
It's easy to get wrapped up.

35:16.882 --> 35:19.049
When's the last time you were?

35:19.084 --> 35:20.550
Wrapped up in a relationship?

35:20.619 --> 35:21.284
Yeah.

35:21.320 --> 35:22.652
I've never done that.

35:22.688 --> 35:23.487
Really?

35:23.555 --> 35:26.389
Mm.

35:26.425 --> 35:27.224
Oh, okay.

35:27.259 --> 35:27.757
Yeah. You're messing with me.

35:27.826 --> 35:28.458
Yeah.

35:28.494 --> 35:30.093
All right, so when?

35:30.129 --> 35:32.395
A few years back.

35:32.431 --> 35:33.897
I thought he was the one.

35:33.932 --> 35:36.533
We both did.

35:36.568 --> 35:41.004
Um, which is why he turned down
a job in LA.

35:41.073 --> 35:43.073
Eventually the guilt just
kinda started chipping away

35:43.108 --> 35:45.108
at the relationship until there
was nothing left,

35:45.177 --> 35:49.012
and suddenly he wasn't
in my life anymore.

35:49.081 --> 35:50.947
I'm sorry.

35:50.983 --> 35:52.949
And after him?

35:53.018 --> 35:55.051
Hasn't really felt
worth it since.

35:55.087 --> 35:57.654
Any of your relationships?

35:57.689 --> 35:59.322
No, yeah, no, I mean...

35:59.391 --> 36:04.828
Just, taking the chance
in the first place.

36:04.863 --> 36:10.267
I'm kind of done with loss,
so...

36:10.302 --> 36:13.637
I know it's hard but I think
it's worth it, every time.

36:13.672 --> 36:15.305
Yeah.

36:15.340 --> 36:17.274
That's 'cause you're
an upbeat kinda guy.

36:17.309 --> 36:19.276
[laughs]

36:24.816 --> 36:25.815
[laughs]

36:25.884 --> 36:27.551
Can I admit something?

36:27.586 --> 36:29.853
Sure.

36:29.888 --> 36:30.987
Okay.

36:31.023 --> 36:36.126
Uh... I wish that
that one kiss we had,

36:36.195 --> 36:38.528
had happened at the beginning
of the summer

36:38.564 --> 36:40.363
instead of at the end.

36:40.399 --> 36:41.665
Wow.

36:41.700 --> 36:43.400
Are you really going there?

36:43.435 --> 36:45.235
[laughs]

36:45.270 --> 36:46.903
I'm serious.

36:49.041 --> 36:50.674
Well.

36:50.709 --> 36:55.278
I guess we both thought we had
the next summer.

36:55.347 --> 36:59.115
Yeah, we did.

36:59.151 --> 37:02.852
But, hey, if any of that was
different, then...

37:02.888 --> 37:05.755
maybe we wouldn't be here.

37:05.824 --> 37:07.924
Maybe you wouldn't be eyeing
that job in London,

37:07.960 --> 37:11.895
which is very exciting,
so... that's the upside.

37:11.930 --> 37:13.163
[laughs]

37:13.198 --> 37:14.731
Look who's being upbeat now.

37:14.800 --> 37:17.334
[laughs]

37:17.369 --> 37:18.401
You ready to get back to work?

37:18.437 --> 37:20.737
Yeah.

37:20.772 --> 37:22.405
You know what?

37:22.441 --> 37:26.910
You're gonna be just fine,
whenever you go.

37:26.945 --> 37:28.411
This town, however?

37:28.447 --> 37:29.713
[grimaces]

37:29.748 --> 37:32.816
I don't think it's gonna do so
well without ya.

38:24.736 --> 38:27.437
[camera shutter snaps]

38:27.472 --> 38:37.280
♪

38:37.316 --> 38:43.620
♪

38:43.655 --> 38:46.523
[camera shutter snaps]

38:48.760 --> 38:51.728
[camera shutter snaps]

39:18.557 --> 39:19.856
[groans groggily]

39:19.891 --> 39:24.961
Just enough caffeine and
chocolate to wake you up.

39:25.030 --> 39:25.695
Thank you.

39:25.731 --> 39:27.530
Mm-hmm.

39:34.172 --> 39:37.440
Did you get your shot?

39:37.476 --> 39:39.642
I think so?

39:39.678 --> 39:41.044
Awesome.

39:47.519 --> 39:49.252
Okay.

39:49.287 --> 39:51.054
How do you look so awake?

39:51.089 --> 39:52.389
I'm exhausted.

39:52.424 --> 39:53.590
Oh, it's adrenaline.

39:53.658 --> 39:54.958
You know?

39:54.993 --> 39:57.494
Luckily, I've got two more days
to round it out, so...

39:57.562 --> 39:58.995
Are you feeling good?

39:59.064 --> 40:00.230
Yeah, I just gotta... I just
gotta keep pushing through.

40:00.265 --> 40:01.898
Just gotta keep shooting
anything and everything.

40:01.933 --> 40:05.301
But, um... I really do feel like
I can breathe, so, thank you.

40:05.337 --> 40:06.970
Good.

40:07.005 --> 40:09.272
Well, if you do feel like
taking a break,

40:09.307 --> 40:10.540
clearing your head,

40:10.575 --> 40:12.175
we're probably going
to hit the rink later on.

40:12.210 --> 40:12.976
[laughs]

40:13.011 --> 40:13.710
I know.

40:13.779 --> 40:15.745
You're gonna ice skate?

40:15.781 --> 40:17.547
Gotta throw the blades
on at least once a year.

40:17.582 --> 40:19.416
[laughs]

40:19.484 --> 40:22.552
I know it was work,
but I had a lot of fun.

40:22.621 --> 40:23.853
Yeah, me too.

40:23.922 --> 40:26.356
[phone rings]

40:26.391 --> 40:27.724
London calling.

40:27.759 --> 40:29.192
Ah. All right.

40:29.227 --> 40:30.693
Do you have to get that?

40:30.729 --> 40:32.962
I mean, they're probably just
setting up the appointment.

40:32.998 --> 40:34.264
Then you have to get that!

40:34.299 --> 40:35.031
I do. I do.

40:35.066 --> 40:35.865
I gotta get out anyway.

40:35.901 --> 40:36.599
You're right, you're right.

40:36.668 --> 40:37.734
Okay. Um...

40:37.769 --> 40:39.369
Thank you.

40:42.808 --> 40:43.440
Hello.

40:43.475 --> 40:44.441
Uh, yes.

40:44.476 --> 40:46.309
Mike Phillips here.

40:46.344 --> 40:47.410
Thank you.

40:47.479 --> 40:49.179
Yes, Josh said that
you'd be calling.

40:57.222 --> 40:59.622
You know,

40:59.658 --> 41:01.090
It's super festive,

41:01.126 --> 41:03.860
and there's so much more snow
than I anticipated.

41:03.895 --> 41:06.496
Then we're basically having
the same Christmas.

41:06.531 --> 41:07.697
[laughs]

41:07.766 --> 41:11.568
Okay, so, did you see
the other submissions.

41:11.603 --> 41:13.336
<i> Yeah, but that was</i>
<i> the first round.</i>

41:13.371 --> 41:16.639
I have no idea what
they're doing now.

41:16.675 --> 41:20.443
Right, right, but... they're
mostly lights on buildings,

41:20.512 --> 41:22.512
sculptures, cityscapes,
that kind of thing?

41:22.547 --> 41:24.714
And high concept,
very artsy.

41:24.783 --> 41:27.050
Well, maybe they're
all too similar.

41:27.085 --> 41:28.918
That's why they're having
a hard time picking.

41:28.954 --> 41:31.354
You still have a little time,
so just keep going.

41:31.389 --> 41:33.122
If it's Christmas
they want...

41:33.158 --> 41:35.592
Well, then I got Christmas.

41:35.627 --> 41:37.060
<i> Thank you.</i>

41:37.095 --> 41:39.028
Talk soon, bye.

41:39.064 --> 41:40.663
Hey.

41:40.699 --> 41:41.731
[sighs]

41:41.766 --> 41:43.433
You ready to go gather
some pinecones?

41:43.468 --> 41:44.133
Huh?

41:44.169 --> 41:45.468
Yeah.

41:45.537 --> 41:46.903
Yeah.

41:46.938 --> 41:47.937
Let's do it.

41:48.540 --> 41:50.206
Let's do it.

41:51.276 --> 41:53.243
-Pine cones.
-Pine cones.

41:54.546 --> 41:56.012
<i> So, these are for ornaments?</i>

41:56.047 --> 41:59.048
Wedding favours... to go along
with the chocolate bells.

41:59.117 --> 42:00.450
Aww.

42:00.485 --> 42:04.120
Oh, well, good thing there are
a lot of them out here.

42:04.189 --> 42:05.755
Do you remember how many hours
you used to spend out here,

42:05.824 --> 42:08.324
playing by the creek?

42:08.360 --> 42:09.859
Yeah, and in it.

42:09.928 --> 42:12.228
[laughs]

42:13.532 --> 42:15.365
Is it weird that I
find it surprising

42:15.400 --> 42:17.634
how beautiful it is
here in the winter?

42:17.669 --> 42:18.868
No, of course not.

42:18.904 --> 42:20.870
You haven't had a chance
to experience it before.

42:20.906 --> 42:22.705
But it's special
all year around,

42:22.741 --> 42:28.611
now that I'm retired I get a
chance to enjoy it all the time.

42:28.647 --> 42:31.281
Why did we never come
here for Christmas?

42:31.349 --> 42:32.048
You did-

42:32.083 --> 42:32.649
What?

42:32.684 --> 42:33.816
You did. Yeah.

42:33.852 --> 42:34.884
When you were five,
you don't remember?

42:34.953 --> 42:36.152
No.

42:36.187 --> 42:37.654
Yeah.

42:37.722 --> 42:41.090
We were only here a few hours
before the furnace went out.

42:41.159 --> 42:41.991
What?

42:42.027 --> 42:43.192
Yeah.

42:43.228 --> 42:45.628
We didn't have a rental,
uh, company back then,

42:45.664 --> 42:47.864
so no one was available
to fix it.

42:47.899 --> 42:49.866
So, we just camped out
by the fireplace.

42:49.901 --> 42:51.067
We camped?

42:51.136 --> 42:52.168
Yup.

42:52.203 --> 42:53.670
Three nights,
right beside the tree.

42:53.705 --> 42:55.338
It was really sweet.

42:55.407 --> 42:58.741
Although, uh, we decided to come
only in the summer after that.

42:58.777 --> 43:00.476
[both laugh]

43:00.512 --> 43:03.079
[sighs]

43:03.114 --> 43:04.647
No, it really is
a magical place.

43:04.716 --> 43:05.782
Mm-hmm.

43:05.817 --> 43:07.216
Probably a bit more magical

43:07.252 --> 43:08.751
with a working furnace though,
right?

43:08.820 --> 43:11.187
[laughs]

43:11.256 --> 43:13.256
I'm so glad you're here.

43:13.291 --> 43:15.592
Yeah.

43:15.627 --> 43:17.493
I wasn't sure how hard it was
going to be to come back,

43:17.529 --> 43:19.028
but, um...

43:19.064 --> 43:21.564
Me too.

43:21.600 --> 43:23.099
And I know that we still have
to talk about what to do

43:23.134 --> 43:24.400
with the house, so...

43:24.436 --> 43:26.369
We can do that later.

43:26.404 --> 43:27.971
You keep saying that.

43:28.006 --> 43:29.172
Well, you haven't slept.

43:29.207 --> 43:31.007
You still need to hand
in your assignment,

43:31.076 --> 43:33.843
so first thing's first, okay?

43:33.878 --> 43:35.311
'Kay.

43:37.015 --> 43:39.515
Do we have enough?

43:39.551 --> 43:40.283
We got plenty.

43:40.318 --> 43:41.751
Okay, good.

43:46.224 --> 43:50.093
Thirty-five silver dusted
pinecones, done.

43:50.128 --> 43:51.995
How's that reindeer coming?

43:52.030 --> 43:53.730
It's a snowman.

43:53.798 --> 43:54.931
Oh, is it?

43:54.966 --> 43:55.999
I knew that.

43:56.034 --> 43:58.001
Thank you.

43:58.036 --> 44:01.270
And, I think I'm done.

44:01.339 --> 44:03.539
Well then, you need to hang it
on the tree.

44:03.608 --> 44:05.942
Oh.

44:09.447 --> 44:13.416
Okay, um...
like here?

44:17.422 --> 44:18.421
Perfect.

44:18.490 --> 44:21.858
Our very first tradition.

44:21.926 --> 44:24.727
Good work.

44:24.763 --> 44:26.229
[sighs]

44:26.264 --> 44:27.697
Did a great job.

44:27.732 --> 44:30.199
[sighs]

44:31.136 --> 44:34.971
So you want me to put each one
of these in one of those boxes?

44:35.006 --> 44:35.872
Yes, dear.

44:35.907 --> 44:37.206
But you know what?

44:37.242 --> 44:38.474
We have two full days to take
care of all of this,

44:38.510 --> 44:40.109
you got plenty of time.

44:40.145 --> 44:43.579
Well, that's why I'm so excited
to fill these little boxes.

44:43.615 --> 44:45.815
Hey, we have to go
to the hotel to do

44:45.850 --> 44:47.517
a couple last minute things.

44:47.552 --> 44:49.318
So, if you wanna
come along...

44:56.161 --> 44:58.027
[sighs]

45:41.673 --> 45:43.639
Hey, Mike?

45:43.675 --> 45:45.708
I might need that break.

45:46.778 --> 45:50.113
♪

45:50.148 --> 45:51.280
Well done.

45:51.316 --> 45:52.548
Hey.

45:52.584 --> 45:53.783
[laughs]

45:53.818 --> 45:55.384
I have to admit, I didn't
see him at first.

45:55.420 --> 45:57.186
So, well done.

45:57.222 --> 45:58.821
I have to admit
that I had help.

45:58.857 --> 46:00.289
Oh, I don't think I was
of much help,

46:00.325 --> 46:01.657
but it was fun.

46:01.726 --> 46:03.426
Well, you'll have fun out
there, too.

46:03.461 --> 46:04.393
Are you guys leaving?

46:04.429 --> 46:05.428
Yeah.

46:05.497 --> 46:06.496
'Cause right now,

46:06.531 --> 46:08.865
we got some hot chocolate
to drink.

46:08.933 --> 46:11.200
-Bye.
-Bye.

46:11.236 --> 46:13.236
The ice is calling.

46:13.271 --> 46:14.504
Let's do this.

46:14.539 --> 46:16.339
[laughs]

46:19.344 --> 46:22.211
I have not done this in years.

46:22.247 --> 46:23.713
Okay, you can't tell,
'cause your... your...

46:23.748 --> 46:25.815
your form is... perfect.

46:25.850 --> 46:30.253
Alright, just give me a minute
to practice.

46:30.288 --> 46:32.255
Okay.

46:32.323 --> 46:34.524
Oh.

46:34.592 --> 46:38.728
Hey, um... Tell me this,
what would you do?

46:38.763 --> 46:41.564
Well that's uh, that's
a very broad question.

46:41.633 --> 46:42.298
Oh, yeah.

46:42.333 --> 46:44.033
About my Dad's house.

46:44.102 --> 46:44.834
You're the property guy.

46:44.903 --> 46:46.002
Would you sell?

46:46.070 --> 46:47.937
Would you rent?

46:48.006 --> 46:52.775
Um, that's a very personal
question.

46:52.811 --> 46:54.811
Yeah, I just don't know.

46:54.879 --> 46:56.279
You know, I mean, had you asked
me a week ago,

46:56.314 --> 46:58.047
I would've said sell.

46:58.082 --> 47:01.150
But now?

47:01.186 --> 47:04.086
Not sure.

47:04.122 --> 47:06.656
Well, probably wait
until you do know,

47:06.691 --> 47:10.960
'cause once it's gone you're
never going to get it back.

47:10.995 --> 47:12.295
So, what do you say, do a little
backwards skate?

47:12.330 --> 47:13.930
[nervously] What? No,
no. No, no, that's...

47:13.965 --> 47:14.997
No, no, that's a terrible idea.

47:15.033 --> 47:15.865
That's... It's easy.

47:15.900 --> 47:16.999
Put your butt down.

47:17.035 --> 47:17.900
I don't wanna.

47:17.969 --> 47:18.601
Do a little spin?

47:18.636 --> 47:19.769
Woah! Woah!

47:19.804 --> 47:20.503
[both laugh]

47:20.572 --> 47:21.771
You're crazy!

47:21.806 --> 47:23.739
I take that as
a compliment.

47:23.775 --> 47:25.308
[laughs]

47:28.246 --> 47:30.213
Mike, I can't.

47:30.248 --> 47:31.214
I'm so sorry.

47:31.249 --> 47:31.614
No, no, no.

47:31.683 --> 47:32.782
I...

47:32.851 --> 47:33.683
Our timing's off.

47:33.718 --> 47:36.052
No, I... I... it's just,
I know.

47:36.120 --> 47:39.655
I was just... look,
I'm... I'm... yeah, I'm sorry.

47:39.724 --> 47:43.025
But just so you know,

47:43.061 --> 47:47.396
I do wish that that kiss had
happened earlier, too.

47:47.432 --> 47:48.531
Yeah?

47:48.566 --> 47:49.866
Yeah.

47:53.171 --> 47:54.537
Okay.

47:54.606 --> 47:56.339
Power lap.

47:56.407 --> 47:57.406
I'm gonna race ya.

47:57.442 --> 47:58.274
Uh-huh?

47:58.309 --> 47:59.208
I'm gonna...

47:59.244 --> 47:59.742
[fumbles]

47:59.777 --> 48:00.409
I'm gonna win.

48:00.478 --> 48:01.210
[laughs]
Okay.

48:01.246 --> 48:03.446
I mean, you're gonna lose.

48:06.217 --> 48:09.285
Whoo, well, probably going
to be sore tom

48:09.320 --> 48:11.621
but worth it.

48:11.656 --> 48:12.288
Yeah?

48:12.357 --> 48:14.390
Glad you took a break?

48:17.095 --> 48:18.995
[sighs]

48:19.063 --> 48:23.666
Spent so much time
with my mom in there.

48:23.701 --> 48:27.236
It's actually where I realized
I wanted to do this.

48:27.272 --> 48:29.071
Be a photographer?

48:33.378 --> 48:35.945
It's also where she found out...

48:39.284 --> 48:43.052
She was sick.

48:43.121 --> 48:45.121
[exhales]

48:45.156 --> 48:48.624
Just makes it really hard to go
back in, you know?

48:48.693 --> 48:51.494
I'm sure it does, but...

48:51.529 --> 48:52.929
If you avoid it all together,

48:52.964 --> 48:57.266
you know, you're avoiding
all the good memories, too.

49:00.772 --> 49:02.271
Yeah.

49:02.307 --> 49:04.807
Let's just see if I can get
this photography thing going.

49:07.011 --> 49:09.312
Then let's finish strong.

49:09.347 --> 49:11.480
This event is... it's different.

49:11.516 --> 49:12.648
Okay?

49:12.717 --> 49:14.550
But there's gonna be people,
a lot of faces.

49:14.585 --> 49:16.819
Oh no, I usually do landscapes
and cityscapes.

49:16.854 --> 49:20.089
I know, I know, but...
this is Christmas, right?

49:20.124 --> 49:22.758
Christmas is all about people.

49:22.794 --> 49:23.926
True, yeah.

49:23.962 --> 49:27.296
Meet me here in the morning?

49:27.332 --> 49:28.497
That all you're gonna tell me?

49:28.533 --> 49:31.600
Uh-huh.

49:31.636 --> 49:33.602
See you in the AM.

49:35.473 --> 49:37.106
Okay, so it's a Christmas fair.

49:37.141 --> 49:39.575
Nope.

49:39.610 --> 49:42.745
Are you seriously not going
to tell me why we're here?

49:42.780 --> 49:45.715
You're just gonna have
to wait for it.

49:45.783 --> 49:47.450
Want a cocoa?

49:47.485 --> 49:48.317
No, are you serious right now?

49:48.386 --> 49:49.919
They have coffee.

49:51.089 --> 49:52.154
I didn't say you'd have
to wait long.

49:52.190 --> 49:53.689
Come on.

49:56.794 --> 49:58.194
[gasps]

49:58.229 --> 50:01.664
Ho, ho, ho!
Merry Christmas!

50:01.699 --> 50:02.365
[laughs]

50:02.400 --> 50:03.599
[surprised]
What?

50:03.634 --> 50:06.635
[shutter snaps]

50:06.704 --> 50:11.474
Oh, my gosh.

50:11.509 --> 50:13.275
This is amazing.

50:13.311 --> 50:14.710
Worth the wait?

50:14.746 --> 50:17.113
Definitely.

50:17.181 --> 50:18.748
Thank you.

50:22.687 --> 50:24.286
Oh, my gosh.

50:24.322 --> 50:26.122
[laughs]

50:27.925 --> 50:31.460
<i> Ho, ho, ho! </i>
<i> Merry Christmas!</i>

50:37.135 --> 50:39.902
[children laughing and chatting]

50:41.606 --> 50:43.205
[shutter snaps]

50:43.241 --> 50:44.740
Aw. Now I really don't know

50:44.776 --> 50:47.176
how you're going
to give all this up.

50:47.211 --> 50:48.310
Me neither.

50:48.346 --> 50:49.745
[laughs]

50:53.718 --> 50:54.583
I got... I'm just gonna...

50:54.652 --> 50:55.985
Yeah.

50:56.821 --> 51:00.723
[shutter snaps]

51:00.758 --> 51:03.626
[laughs]

51:03.661 --> 51:13.502
<i> [Instrumental version of</i>
<i> "Jolly Old Saint Nicholas"]</i>
<i> ♪</i>

51:16.674 --> 51:21.677
[shutter snaps]

51:25.416 --> 51:27.249
[laughs]

52:01.586 --> 52:03.385
Not quite done?

52:03.421 --> 52:04.186
Uh, no.

52:04.222 --> 52:06.322
I'm, uh... I'm almost done,

52:06.357 --> 52:10.426
I just... this is so different
from what I normally do,

52:10.461 --> 52:13.229
and I feel like he really liked
my initial direction,

52:13.264 --> 52:15.965
so I just...

52:16.000 --> 52:19.535
But he had you redo it,
right?

52:19.570 --> 52:21.937
That's a good point, yeah.

52:22.006 --> 52:23.339
I don't know, I just feel
like this is...

52:23.374 --> 52:26.442
So different than
where I started.

52:26.477 --> 52:28.277
The light of Christmas,
that's the title.

52:28.312 --> 52:29.245
Right?

52:29.280 --> 52:30.279
Mm-hmm.

52:30.348 --> 52:33.682
So, it... it's different
for everyone.

52:33.718 --> 52:35.184
It's personal.

52:35.253 --> 52:37.753
That's what makes it special.

52:37.788 --> 52:40.756
So, as long as your light
is coming through,

52:40.825 --> 52:43.926
I don't think you can
go wrong.

52:55.306 --> 52:57.840
[laughs]

52:58.242 --> 53:01.043
[taps key loudly]

53:01.112 --> 53:02.478
Good work.

53:09.921 --> 53:12.254
I... I've never seen anything
like this tree.

53:12.290 --> 53:14.757
Well, I warned you that it might
be a little bit over the top.

53:14.825 --> 53:16.825
No, it's beautiful.

53:16.861 --> 53:19.662
In fact, your whole house
is beautiful.

53:19.697 --> 53:22.264
Oh, well, it's a little bit
different than your dad's place,

53:22.300 --> 53:24.800
but we're happy here.

53:24.835 --> 53:25.501
Yeah.

53:25.536 --> 53:27.102
I think it's perfect.

53:27.138 --> 53:28.771
Thanks for coming over, Sam.

53:28.806 --> 53:30.940
Here, let's sit down.

53:33.878 --> 53:35.511
[sighs]

53:35.546 --> 53:38.013
I want to talk to you
about something important.

53:38.082 --> 53:40.749
Sure.

53:40.785 --> 53:43.485
I know that I would have loved
your mother.

53:43.521 --> 53:47.289
I mean, she sounds like such
an amazing woman.

53:47.325 --> 53:49.925
And I'll never try
to take her place,

53:49.961 --> 53:53.529
or what you guys had.

53:53.598 --> 53:56.098
And I want you to know
how lucky I feel

53:56.133 --> 53:58.601
to be marrying into this family.

53:58.669 --> 54:06.108
So, I'm just hoping that maybe
you'll be my maid of honour.

54:06.143 --> 54:07.610
Me?

54:07.678 --> 54:09.678
There's nothing extra you have
to do, I promise.

54:09.714 --> 54:13.082
And I've already set a couple
dresses aside, just in case.

54:13.117 --> 54:14.617
[laughs]

54:14.652 --> 54:20.789
But, it's so important for me
to have you be a part of this.

54:20.825 --> 54:24.393
I'd love to.

54:24.428 --> 54:25.294
Really?

54:25.329 --> 54:26.328
Yeah.

54:26.364 --> 54:28.330
[laughs]

54:28.366 --> 54:29.031
Thank you.

54:29.100 --> 54:30.466
Thank you.

54:31.502 --> 54:32.801
Oh, I am so happy.

54:32.870 --> 54:35.170
[laughs]

54:35.206 --> 54:37.706
Wow.

54:37.775 --> 54:40.109
Are you still up for helping me
finish those wedding favours?

54:40.144 --> 54:41.477
I am, I am, yes.

54:41.545 --> 54:42.544
Let's go.

54:42.580 --> 54:43.512
Okay.

54:45.016 --> 54:47.416
It sounds like an incredible
opportunity, and a...

54:47.451 --> 54:49.785
a pace that I'd definitely be
up for.

54:49.820 --> 54:50.853
Great.

54:50.888 --> 54:52.921
I look forward to hearing
from you.

54:53.924 --> 54:55.658
How'd it go?

54:55.693 --> 54:57.259
Good. Good.

54:57.295 --> 54:59.128
I mean, he's gonna get back
to me later on today.

54:59.196 --> 55:00.763
But, uh.

55:00.831 --> 55:03.365
Yeah, it went...
went pretty well.

55:03.401 --> 55:04.500
Are you sure?

55:04.535 --> 55:06.101
You don't look like it did.

55:06.137 --> 55:07.636
I don't know.

55:07.705 --> 55:09.772
It's a lot to process.

55:09.840 --> 55:12.074
Well, you've always
been decisive.

55:12.143 --> 55:15.778
So I think you just gotta figure
out what it is holding you back,

55:15.813 --> 55:19.048
and go from there.

55:25.056 --> 55:26.388
I've never done moulds before,

55:26.424 --> 55:28.490
but I have been baking
gingerbread waffles

55:28.526 --> 55:29.858
every Christmas morning

55:29.894 --> 55:33.295
since I was about nine, so...
if you're interested...

55:33.331 --> 55:35.297
I will definitely be there.

55:35.366 --> 55:38.300
So I heard you got some
good pictures of Santa today.

55:38.336 --> 55:40.135
Oh, yeah.

55:40.171 --> 55:42.938
You know, the whole thing
was just amazing.

55:42.973 --> 55:44.406
Well, it's always more special
when you share it

55:44.442 --> 55:45.607
with someone you care about.

55:45.676 --> 55:46.809
Yeah.

55:46.844 --> 55:49.011
Oh wait, do you mean Mike?

55:49.046 --> 55:50.446
No, no.

55:50.481 --> 55:51.547
No, we... uh...

55:51.582 --> 55:52.481
[fumbles uncomfortably]

55:52.550 --> 55:53.248
We're friends.

55:53.284 --> 55:54.350
Old friends.

55:54.385 --> 55:55.517
We're old friends,
so, but... Any...

55:55.553 --> 55:57.453
Anyway, he's thinking about
moving, so...

55:57.488 --> 56:00.422
Yeah, but he's here now.

56:00.458 --> 56:03.192
Yeah, but you know?

56:03.227 --> 56:07.863
You know what, I think
it's just... our timing
was always off.

56:07.898 --> 56:12.701
When we were kids,
and then again now.

56:12.737 --> 56:16.839
But something tells me that
those feelings are still there.

56:17.808 --> 56:19.708
Mmm.

56:19.744 --> 56:21.243
Smells amazing in here.

56:21.278 --> 56:23.645
Hey, there's my groom.

56:23.681 --> 56:25.614
So now I think it's time
to celebrate.

56:25.649 --> 56:29.518
Oh, we're gonna be celebrating
plenty tomorrow.

56:29.553 --> 56:31.253
Yeah, you and I,
but this is for Sam.

56:31.322 --> 56:32.955
For me? Why?

56:32.990 --> 56:34.323
Well, you turned in
your assignment.

56:34.358 --> 56:34.990
Didn't you?

56:35.059 --> 56:35.991
Yeah.

56:36.060 --> 56:36.892
I'm not gonna hear
if I get the job

56:36.927 --> 56:37.960
till Christmas day, though.

56:38.028 --> 56:39.695
But you gave it everything
you got,

56:39.730 --> 56:41.196
and that's all that matters.

56:41.232 --> 56:42.631
So?

56:42.666 --> 56:44.400
Gourmet hot chocolate
at the hotel?

56:44.435 --> 56:45.634
What do you say?

56:45.703 --> 56:47.069
Are the carollers there?

56:47.104 --> 56:50.172
Yeah, so we better hurry,
or we might not get a spot.

56:50.207 --> 56:51.740
Apparently, it's kind of
a thing.

56:51.776 --> 56:53.008
Okay.

56:53.077 --> 56:53.876
I just wanna try one of these
for the road.

56:53.911 --> 56:55.110
Oh.

56:55.179 --> 56:56.011
What?

56:56.046 --> 56:56.745
She's the boss.
She says no.

56:56.814 --> 56:58.013
Those are for the wedding.

56:58.048 --> 56:58.847
Okay, okay.

56:58.883 --> 57:00.315
We'll get some later,
right?

57:00.351 --> 57:01.183
When we get back.

57:01.252 --> 57:01.917
[cackles]

57:01.952 --> 57:02.951
Let's go.

57:02.987 --> 57:04.286
[laughs]

57:06.724 --> 57:10.125
♪ O come all ye faithful, ♪

57:10.161 --> 57:14.062
♪ joyful and triumphant ♪

57:14.098 --> 57:16.198
♪ O come ye, O come ye... ♪

57:16.233 --> 57:17.933
Oh, wow.

57:17.968 --> 57:19.268
I don't know how they're
possibly going to add

57:19.303 --> 57:21.437
more decorations for tomorrow.

57:21.472 --> 57:24.039
Oh, I'm sure they could fit a
few more poinsettias in here.

57:24.074 --> 57:26.909
Oh, definitely.

57:26.944 --> 57:31.380
♪ Born the king of angels, ♪

57:31.415 --> 57:35.684
Your timing seems pretty good
to me right now.

57:43.294 --> 57:45.894
♪

57:45.930 --> 57:47.596
So, that is why it is important
for us

57:47.665 --> 57:50.165
to be able to promote
local artists.

57:50.201 --> 57:52.334
So almost everyone
that you see in here,

57:52.403 --> 57:57.639
is either from here
or lives here.

57:57.675 --> 57:59.007
Umm...

57:59.043 --> 58:02.144
Won't you excuse me
for a moment please?

58:06.884 --> 58:07.983
Hi.

58:08.018 --> 58:09.151
Hi.

58:09.186 --> 58:12.254
You must be Elizabeth's
daughter, Samantha.

58:12.289 --> 58:13.489
Right?

58:13.524 --> 58:14.857
Forgive me.

58:14.892 --> 58:19.161
As I'm looking at you,
it's like staring right at her.

58:19.230 --> 58:21.697
You think so?

58:21.732 --> 58:23.732
I never thought so.

58:23.801 --> 58:26.001
Thank you,
that's nice to hear.

58:28.973 --> 58:31.173
[sighs]

58:31.208 --> 58:34.476
We spent so much time
in here.

58:34.512 --> 58:35.944
You remember?

58:35.980 --> 58:38.380
Yes, I do.

58:38.415 --> 58:43.318
It actually inspired me
to follow in her footsteps.

58:43.354 --> 58:46.421
Well, your mom
was very talented.

58:46.457 --> 58:50.492
I used to always want her
to submit more of her work.

58:50.528 --> 58:53.462
But, she made it very clear.

58:53.497 --> 58:55.297
Life came first.

58:55.366 --> 58:57.065
You guys.

58:57.101 --> 58:58.000
Really?

58:58.035 --> 58:59.368
Mm-hmm.

59:00.271 --> 59:01.370
[laughs]

59:01.438 --> 59:04.606
That's what made her work
so beautiful.

59:04.642 --> 59:10.812
And that is also what I will
remember most about her.

59:10.848 --> 59:13.248
Please, won't you have a seat?

59:23.694 --> 59:27.863
I've been wanting to come in
here for days, but...

59:27.932 --> 59:28.697
I know.

59:28.766 --> 59:29.798
It was hard.

59:29.833 --> 59:30.799
Listen.

59:30.868 --> 59:33.569
I know that it's been
a long time,

59:33.604 --> 59:37.439
but I am so sorry
for your loss.

59:37.474 --> 59:40.609
Thank you.

59:40.678 --> 59:43.545
But I'm so glad that you share
the same passion,

59:43.581 --> 59:46.014
and the same love of art.

59:46.083 --> 59:48.617
Like your mom.

59:48.652 --> 59:53.322
And you can see her
in everything you do.

59:53.357 --> 59:56.291
And that is a gift.

59:56.327 --> 59:57.426
[sighs tearfully]

59:57.461 --> 59:59.361
Yeah.

59:59.396 --> 1:00:01.029
It is.

1:00:03.968 --> 1:00:07.603
Oh, listen, I'd love it
if you would like

1:00:07.671 --> 1:00:09.905
to bring in your work
sometime.

1:00:09.974 --> 1:00:13.175
I would be more than happy
to take a look at it.

1:00:13.243 --> 1:00:14.743
Thank you.

1:00:14.778 --> 1:00:17.546
That means the world.

1:00:19.950 --> 1:00:22.250
I'm really glad you came in.

1:00:25.589 --> 1:00:26.388
Excuse me.

1:00:26.423 --> 1:00:27.856
Yeah.

1:00:31.061 --> 1:00:45.140
<i> ♪</i>

1:00:45.175 --> 1:00:47.709
Okay, so I know we're still
putting the deal together.

1:00:47.778 --> 1:00:49.745
But congrats on the job!

1:00:49.780 --> 1:00:50.812
This is great, right?

1:00:50.881 --> 1:00:51.847
Yes.

1:00:51.882 --> 1:00:52.914
Yeah. Thank you.

1:00:52.983 --> 1:00:56.018
Um. Look man, I owe you.

1:00:56.053 --> 1:00:57.486
But uh...

1:00:57.521 --> 1:00:59.388
What?

1:00:59.423 --> 1:01:01.757
It's just... look.

1:01:01.825 --> 1:01:03.825
You know that I would love
to work with you again.

1:01:03.861 --> 1:01:07.963
You... you don't wanna move?

1:01:07.998 --> 1:01:10.932
I don't think so, no.

1:01:11.001 --> 1:01:12.701
I get it.

1:01:12.736 --> 1:01:14.036
You do?

1:01:14.104 --> 1:01:16.405
It's a lot to leave.

1:01:16.440 --> 1:01:17.572
Yeah.

1:01:17.608 --> 1:01:21.476
I mean, my family,
and you know, this town.

1:01:21.512 --> 1:01:23.512
And the rest of it.

1:01:24.948 --> 1:01:26.281
What?

1:01:27.051 --> 1:01:28.350
Hey.

1:01:28.385 --> 1:01:30.452
I've seen you fall for a few
girls through the years.

1:01:30.487 --> 1:01:32.954
Sam's the only one you've
fallen for twice.

1:01:32.990 --> 1:01:34.256
It's...

1:01:34.291 --> 1:01:36.124
What?

1:01:36.193 --> 1:01:37.759
You talked about her.

1:01:37.828 --> 1:01:40.796
A lot.

1:01:40.831 --> 1:01:44.232
When I left, I had a whole lot
to move for.

1:01:44.268 --> 1:01:47.502
Hannah was there, work,
family.

1:01:47.538 --> 1:01:51.073
Everything you love is here.

1:01:51.108 --> 1:01:55.811
Okay, everything except me.
I won't be here, but...

1:01:55.846 --> 1:01:58.113
So yeah.

1:01:58.148 --> 1:02:00.282
I get it.

1:02:00.317 --> 1:02:02.384
Thanks, man.

1:02:04.888 --> 1:02:14.796
♪

1:02:20.838 --> 1:02:23.839
Oh, no, no, no, no, no,
no, no, no,

1:02:23.874 --> 1:02:25.574
no, no, no, no, no.

1:02:27.644 --> 1:02:29.077
Uh, hi, Dad.

1:02:29.113 --> 1:02:30.712
Yeah, I'm so sorry
to bother you,

1:02:30.748 --> 1:02:32.214
but the um, it's leaking.

1:02:32.282 --> 1:02:34.950
The ceiling is leaking again.

1:02:34.985 --> 1:02:35.550
Okay.

1:02:35.586 --> 1:02:37.452
Yep.

1:02:37.521 --> 1:02:39.421
I'll... You call the handyman,
I'll get a bucket.

1:02:39.490 --> 1:02:40.822
Okay, bye.

1:02:46.530 --> 1:02:47.763
That'll do.

1:02:56.273 --> 1:02:58.807
[sighs]

1:03:04.114 --> 1:03:05.347
Right.

1:03:06.550 --> 1:03:09.184
[heavy clunking]

1:03:42.319 --> 1:03:43.285
[small chuckle]

1:04:23.594 --> 1:04:24.860
Help has arrived.

1:04:24.895 --> 1:04:25.694
I'm so glad you're back.

1:04:25.729 --> 1:04:27.028
Did you get a handyman?

1:04:27.064 --> 1:04:30.065
Well, I got a not-so-handyman
that's very helpful.

1:04:35.839 --> 1:04:37.706
All right. Let's fix this.

1:04:42.079 --> 1:04:43.545
I found this-

1:04:43.580 --> 1:04:44.813
Oh, wow.

1:04:44.848 --> 1:04:50.218
-in the attic from our
first Christmas here.

1:04:50.254 --> 1:04:52.888
And then I found this,

1:04:52.923 --> 1:04:55.023
that I made for Mom here,
remember?

1:04:55.058 --> 1:04:58.226
I remember this.

1:04:58.262 --> 1:05:00.228
Wow.

1:05:00.264 --> 1:05:07.869
I just think there are so
many memories here, and...

1:05:07.905 --> 1:05:10.505
I don't want to let them go.

1:05:10.540 --> 1:05:12.841
Me either.

1:05:12.876 --> 1:05:13.775
Really?

1:05:13.810 --> 1:05:14.809
Yeah.

1:05:17.414 --> 1:05:20.048
Who else is going to come
and play in the creek,

1:05:20.083 --> 1:05:22.918
or come for Christmas? Huh?

1:05:28.492 --> 1:05:29.557
[sighs]

1:05:29.626 --> 1:05:31.960
All right, this time,
definitely fixed.

1:05:31.995 --> 1:05:34.763
Are you sure we shouldn't
call a professional?

1:05:34.798 --> 1:05:37.732
Hey, I'm a professional
jack-of-all-trades.

1:05:37.801 --> 1:05:39.034
Is that even a thing?

1:05:39.102 --> 1:05:40.568
Mm-hmm.

1:05:40.604 --> 1:05:44.005
Are you sure this wasn't just
an excuse to get back here?

1:05:44.041 --> 1:05:45.040
[laughs]

1:05:45.075 --> 1:05:46.074
Dad!

1:05:46.143 --> 1:05:47.008
I mean, I'm just saying.

1:05:47.044 --> 1:05:48.176
Look.

1:05:48.211 --> 1:05:51.212
Um... I think there was a...
a second leak

1:05:51.248 --> 1:05:52.847
that I didn't see
the first time.

1:05:52.883 --> 1:05:55.717
But it's definitely
all patched up now.

1:05:55.786 --> 1:05:58.353
Good.

1:05:58.422 --> 1:06:02.290
'Cause we're keeping the house.

1:06:02.359 --> 1:06:03.558
You are?

1:06:03.593 --> 1:06:06.695
All right, thanks
for coming by Mike.

1:06:06.763 --> 1:06:08.330
Take care of yourself.

1:06:08.398 --> 1:06:09.531
See you tomorrow, sir.

1:06:09.566 --> 1:06:10.598
I am so sorry.

1:06:10.634 --> 1:06:12.334
He's kind of embarrassing
sometimes.

1:06:12.369 --> 1:06:13.568
It's fine.

1:06:13.637 --> 1:06:16.237
I really did try and fix it
last time, though.

1:06:16.273 --> 1:06:17.539
I'm glad it happened.

1:06:17.574 --> 1:06:20.275
'Cause it gave me a chance
to ask you in person.

1:06:20.344 --> 1:06:21.743
Ask me what?

1:06:21.812 --> 1:06:24.512
If you wanted to be my date
to the wedding.

1:06:24.581 --> 1:06:25.680
I know.

1:06:25.749 --> 1:06:27.582
I know what you said
about my leaving.

1:06:27.617 --> 1:06:29.117
And I... I get it.

1:06:29.186 --> 1:06:31.653
I've been thinking a lot,
and I don't think this is

1:06:31.688 --> 1:06:33.955
the right time for me
to move anyways.

1:06:35.258 --> 1:06:37.592
You're not going to London now?

1:06:40.130 --> 1:06:42.731
Okay... Um...

1:06:45.102 --> 1:06:47.268
Does it have anything
to do with...

1:06:47.337 --> 1:06:47.802
With...

1:06:47.838 --> 1:06:48.336
No, us?

1:06:48.372 --> 1:06:49.838
No. No.

1:06:49.873 --> 1:06:51.172
Okay.

1:06:51.208 --> 1:06:53.141
No. Like you said, this place
is hard to leave.

1:06:53.210 --> 1:06:56.811
And... I mean, who else is gonna
move the snowman next year?

1:06:56.847 --> 1:06:59.447
Right?

1:06:59.483 --> 1:07:01.416
So, what do you say?

1:07:01.451 --> 1:07:03.251
Uh... I don't know.

1:07:03.286 --> 1:07:06.788
I mean, I'm kinda in the wedding
now, so...

1:07:06.823 --> 1:07:08.656
Is that a no?

1:07:08.692 --> 1:07:13.495
No. Just means you're gonna have
to meet me there.

1:07:19.236 --> 1:07:19.801
Awesome.

1:07:19.870 --> 1:07:21.836
[laughs]

1:07:22.572 --> 1:07:23.671
Bye.

1:07:26.410 --> 1:07:28.276
Right this way.

1:07:28.311 --> 1:07:31.146
And you can set up in there,
and we'll be right in.

1:07:31.181 --> 1:07:33.782
Thank you.

1:07:33.817 --> 1:07:36.017
You ready for some pampering?

1:07:36.053 --> 1:07:37.685
I am, I am, but you really
don't have to do this.

1:07:37.721 --> 1:07:39.120
It... it's your big day.

1:07:39.156 --> 1:07:40.588
I wanted to.

1:07:40.624 --> 1:07:41.823
Aw....

1:07:41.892 --> 1:07:45.160
Well, I wanted to get you
something, too.

1:07:45.195 --> 1:07:47.962
You didn't have
to get me anything.

1:07:47.998 --> 1:07:49.164
But thank you.

1:07:49.199 --> 1:07:51.499
I know I'm not the most seasoned
maid of honour,

1:07:51.568 --> 1:07:56.004
but... I'm pretty sure you need
something old.

1:08:05.615 --> 1:08:07.949
Oh. That's beautiful.

1:08:08.885 --> 1:08:11.519
That is beautiful.

1:08:11.555 --> 1:08:15.423
Um, I actually made it
for my mom.

1:08:15.459 --> 1:08:17.992
When I was like ten.

1:08:22.666 --> 1:08:23.531
Are you sure?

1:08:23.567 --> 1:08:25.433
Yeah.

1:08:25.469 --> 1:08:28.269
Yeah, you know...

1:08:28.305 --> 1:08:30.538
We're really lucky to have
found you, too.

1:08:40.250 --> 1:08:41.149
Well, let's...

1:08:41.184 --> 1:08:42.517
Yeah.

1:08:42.586 --> 1:08:43.751
Let's... let's do this.

1:08:43.787 --> 1:08:48.223
Let's also consider it
something borrowed.

1:08:48.258 --> 1:08:55.830
Because I look forward to
when I can give it back to you.

1:08:55.866 --> 1:08:57.398
'Kay.

1:09:00.637 --> 1:09:02.470
Okay, so other than handing
them the rings...

1:09:02.539 --> 1:09:04.539
Just enjoy the moment.

1:09:04.574 --> 1:09:08.309
Take it all in, and keep your
father relaxed.

1:09:08.345 --> 1:09:09.244
What?

1:09:09.279 --> 1:09:10.178
I'm relaxed.

1:09:10.247 --> 1:09:11.713
Well, your guests are here,

1:09:11.748 --> 1:09:14.349
so I'm just going to make sure
everyone is seated.

1:09:14.384 --> 1:09:15.183
Sure.

1:09:15.218 --> 1:09:15.917
Thank you.

1:09:15.952 --> 1:09:17.185
Thank you.

1:09:18.955 --> 1:09:19.921
So?

1:09:22.726 --> 1:09:25.560
Are you nervous?

1:09:25.629 --> 1:09:30.064
Well, I kind of thought I would
be, but no, I'm...I'm good.

1:09:30.100 --> 1:09:32.433
How about you?

1:09:32.502 --> 1:09:34.002
Same.

1:09:34.638 --> 1:09:36.271
That makes me happy.

1:09:36.306 --> 1:09:37.138
Yeah.

1:09:37.174 --> 1:09:38.940
Me too.

1:09:42.712 --> 1:09:44.012
It's time.

1:09:46.583 --> 1:09:48.016
You ready?

1:09:48.051 --> 1:09:48.616
Yeah?

1:09:48.685 --> 1:09:49.117
I'm ready.

1:09:49.186 --> 1:09:49.851
Okay.

1:09:49.886 --> 1:09:52.787
Let's do it.

