1:11:53.443 --> 1:11:57.345
Okay, so, admittedly, this was
my first Christmas wedding.

1:11:57.380 --> 1:11:58.746
I thought it was pretty perfect.

1:11:58.782 --> 1:12:03.051
I agree, but I'm biased, so...

1:12:03.086 --> 1:12:06.854
I guess um, here's to the rest
of the night

1:12:06.923 --> 1:12:08.323
being perfect as well?

1:12:08.391 --> 1:12:08.890
Oh.

1:12:08.925 --> 1:12:09.757
Woah!

1:12:09.793 --> 1:12:12.894
[laughs]

1:12:12.962 --> 1:12:14.796
You a professional dancer now,
too?

1:12:14.831 --> 1:12:15.596
How would you tell?

1:12:15.632 --> 1:12:16.597
No.

1:12:26.543 --> 1:12:27.842
Oh, you know what,

1:12:27.877 --> 1:12:30.345
I have to go help set up
some bridal photos, so...

1:12:30.380 --> 1:12:31.446
What?

1:12:31.481 --> 1:12:33.648
They hired another photographer?

1:12:33.683 --> 1:12:35.049
Cute.

1:12:35.085 --> 1:12:37.618
I think they've had enough of me
working for a while.

1:12:37.687 --> 1:12:39.487
Good.

1:12:39.522 --> 1:12:41.189
Okay, well, I'll grab
some appetizers.

1:12:41.257 --> 1:12:42.323
Meet you back
at the table.

1:12:42.359 --> 1:12:43.458
Sure.

1:12:47.797 --> 1:12:49.297
I'm gonna go.

1:12:49.332 --> 1:12:50.164
Okay.

1:12:50.200 --> 1:12:52.133
Like, right now.

1:12:52.168 --> 1:12:53.434
Okay.

1:12:55.672 --> 1:12:56.537
Okay.

1:12:58.508 --> 1:12:59.207
Hi.

1:12:59.275 --> 1:13:00.608
Hi!

1:13:00.643 --> 1:13:02.910
If there are any specific family
photos you want to get,

1:13:02.946 --> 1:13:06.280
let me know, otherwise
she's just gonna do candids.

1:13:06.316 --> 1:13:07.682
I think candids sound great.

1:13:07.717 --> 1:13:08.449
Sam?

1:13:08.485 --> 1:13:09.717
Yeah. No, I love candids.

1:13:09.753 --> 1:13:11.052
Great.

1:13:11.087 --> 1:13:13.020
Oh, I just need to grab you
for one more thing.

1:13:13.056 --> 1:13:13.755
Ah.

1:13:13.823 --> 1:13:15.022
[laughs]

1:13:16.993 --> 1:13:19.727
Oh, hey, you did an excellent
job out there.

1:13:19.763 --> 1:13:21.295
Well, thanks.

1:13:21.364 --> 1:13:22.497
We're so happy you guys
could make it.

1:13:22.532 --> 1:13:23.965
Ah, so are we.

1:13:24.000 --> 1:13:25.333
Yeah.

1:13:25.368 --> 1:13:26.934
And I have to say, we're pretty
glad he's not moving.

1:13:26.970 --> 1:13:27.935
Oh, I bet you are.

1:13:27.971 --> 1:13:29.470
Yeah.

1:13:29.539 --> 1:13:32.707
It was a pretty big opportunity,
so, uh, he must really like you.

1:13:32.742 --> 1:13:35.143
Oh, yeah... no, no,
he's not staying for me.

1:13:35.178 --> 1:13:37.578
He's staying for the town,
and for you guys.

1:13:37.614 --> 1:13:39.547
[flustered] Yeah,
oh, yeah, well, you know,

1:13:39.582 --> 1:13:41.182
he likes to keep
everybody happy.

1:13:41.217 --> 1:13:43.284
That's true.

1:13:43.319 --> 1:13:45.153
But hopefully we'll see
a lot more of you.

1:13:45.221 --> 1:13:46.621
Yeah.

1:13:46.656 --> 1:13:48.890
If my favourite Christmas
music wasn't enough,

1:13:48.925 --> 1:13:51.058
there's gonna be sparklers too.

1:13:51.127 --> 1:13:52.827
Come on.

1:14:02.772 --> 1:14:09.544
<i> [Jazzy Christmas music]</i>
♪

1:14:09.612 --> 1:14:10.445
Hey.

1:14:10.480 --> 1:14:11.145
Hey.

1:14:11.181 --> 1:14:12.280
Sorry I took so long.

1:14:12.315 --> 1:14:14.515
I had to ask your dad
a rental question,

1:14:14.551 --> 1:14:16.217
just 'cause it's, like,
time sensitive.

1:14:16.252 --> 1:14:17.852
But, I did manage to get
the good apps

1:14:17.887 --> 1:14:18.920
before they were taken.

1:14:18.955 --> 1:14:21.556
Thank you.

1:14:21.591 --> 1:14:23.724
Are you okay?

1:14:23.760 --> 1:14:25.560
I think you should go.

1:14:25.628 --> 1:14:28.362
You wanted to go.

1:14:28.431 --> 1:14:30.798
Is... is this about London?

1:14:30.867 --> 1:14:33.167
That was... that
was just an offer.

1:14:33.203 --> 1:14:34.569
It was an opportunity,
and it was a really,

1:14:34.637 --> 1:14:37.238
really good one.

1:14:37.273 --> 1:14:40.675
Are you... are you trying
to get rid of me already?

1:14:40.710 --> 1:14:43.377
That's, no, that's not
what I'm...

1:14:47.217 --> 1:14:49.884
Did they say something?

1:14:56.259 --> 1:14:57.925
I know that there are probably
many different reasons

1:14:57.961 --> 1:14:59.861
that you would
want to stay here.

1:14:59.896 --> 1:15:07.568
Your family, the town, and us,
but... before I came back,

1:15:07.604 --> 1:15:09.237
you wanted to go, right?

1:15:09.305 --> 1:15:12.673
You... you... you wanted
to go and do something new
for yourself.

1:15:12.742 --> 1:15:14.208
I... I did, but...

1:15:14.244 --> 1:15:16.010
And I think you should do that.

1:15:16.045 --> 1:15:17.445
Right?

1:15:18.915 --> 1:15:24.919
Mike, this is about
what makes you happy.

1:15:24.954 --> 1:15:26.854
So, what are you saying?

1:15:26.890 --> 1:15:30.124
I don't want you
to have any regrets.

1:15:30.159 --> 1:15:31.559
You're just assuming
that I would.

1:15:31.594 --> 1:15:33.127
Because I've been here before.

1:15:33.196 --> 1:15:35.263
You know you don't think
that you're gonna be giving

1:15:35.331 --> 1:15:37.365
anything up in the moment,
but then over time,

1:15:37.400 --> 1:15:38.933
it just...

1:15:41.871 --> 1:15:43.871
I don't want that.

1:15:43.907 --> 1:15:46.073
For either of us.

1:15:46.109 --> 1:15:47.475
Why are you trying
to sabotage this?

1:15:47.510 --> 1:15:53.180
I'm not, I just...
think our timing is off.

1:15:53.216 --> 1:15:55.182
Again.

1:15:55.785 --> 1:15:58.119
Look, I get it.

1:15:58.154 --> 1:15:59.120
Okay?

1:15:59.155 --> 1:16:01.422
We've... we've both lost.

1:16:01.491 --> 1:16:03.824
But you can't hide behind
that forever.

1:16:03.860 --> 1:16:05.159
You can't always take
the safe way out

1:16:05.194 --> 1:16:09.463
because you don't want
to risk anything.

1:16:09.532 --> 1:16:11.499
Pfft.

1:16:13.269 --> 1:16:16.437
<i> Ladies and gentlemen,</i>
<i> it's time to cut the cake.</i>

1:16:16.472 --> 1:16:20.808
<i> [applause]</i>

1:16:20.843 --> 1:16:21.442
I gotta...

1:16:21.477 --> 1:16:22.143
Sam.

1:16:22.178 --> 1:16:23.444
...get back in there.

1:16:23.479 --> 1:16:24.445
Sam.

1:16:24.480 --> 1:16:25.479
I'm gonna...

1:16:32.655 --> 1:16:35.256
Now, some of
these are a little silly

1:16:35.291 --> 1:16:36.057
[chuckles]

1:16:36.092 --> 1:16:37.592
But, I hope you like 'em.

1:16:37.627 --> 1:16:42.029
We're gonna love them, but...

1:16:42.098 --> 1:16:43.564
I wanna do this one.

1:16:43.600 --> 1:16:45.633
Let's do it.

1:16:45.702 --> 1:16:46.934
Merry Christmas.

1:16:47.003 --> 1:16:50.471
Oh, guys, I told you not
to get me anything.

1:16:50.506 --> 1:16:52.974
I know, but it's important
to us.

1:17:00.083 --> 1:17:02.316
What is this?

1:17:05.555 --> 1:17:08.356
Oh... This is about the house.

1:17:08.391 --> 1:17:12.460
Mm-hmm.

1:17:12.528 --> 1:17:16.664
You signed the house over to me?

1:17:16.699 --> 1:17:18.132
What?

1:17:18.167 --> 1:17:20.701
Helen and I really want you
to have the house.

1:17:20.737 --> 1:17:21.836
And I know your mother

1:17:21.871 --> 1:17:24.372
would want you to have
the house, too.

1:17:26.275 --> 1:17:28.175
Guys, I don't even...
I don't...

1:17:28.244 --> 1:17:29.143
[cries]

1:17:29.212 --> 1:17:29.944
Thank you.

1:17:29.979 --> 1:17:30.778
I don't know what to say.

1:17:30.847 --> 1:17:31.846
Oh, Merry Christmas.

1:17:31.881 --> 1:17:32.880
Merry Christmas.

1:17:32.915 --> 1:17:34.715
It's so nice to have you here.

1:17:34.784 --> 1:17:36.651
Thank you.

1:17:38.621 --> 1:17:40.688
You know, I think this might
be the first time ever

1:17:40.723 --> 1:17:44.158
that you haven't devoured your
donut before we left the café.

1:17:44.193 --> 1:17:46.460
Hey, well, if you don't want
it, I can always...

1:17:46.496 --> 1:17:49.163
All right, never mind,
I don't want it.

1:17:49.198 --> 1:17:51.298
You feeling okay?

1:17:51.334 --> 1:17:55.169
Yeah, no, I... I just didn't
sleep much last night.

1:17:55.238 --> 1:17:56.971
Is this about Sam?

1:17:57.040 --> 1:17:59.340
Well, what about Sam?

1:17:59.375 --> 1:18:01.475
Oh, did I mess things up
by mentioning that...

1:18:01.511 --> 1:18:02.843
Dad.

1:18:02.912 --> 1:18:05.413
You were just stating a fact,
you know?

1:18:05.448 --> 1:18:09.984
It was a good opportunity,
but... It's all good.

1:18:13.389 --> 1:18:16.724
No it's not all good.

1:18:16.759 --> 1:18:17.725
Not even a little.

1:18:17.794 --> 1:18:18.693
<i> No.</i>

1:18:18.728 --> 1:18:20.661
No.

1:18:23.800 --> 1:18:25.399
She's amazing.

1:18:27.336 --> 1:18:30.404
I can't believe you worked
with Mike on this.

1:18:30.440 --> 1:18:32.506
He said you guys were talking
about rental stuff.

1:18:32.542 --> 1:18:34.041
Yeah, he knew a guy that could
help us out last minute

1:18:34.077 --> 1:18:36.343
to get it done.

1:18:36.379 --> 1:18:37.978
Of course he does.

1:18:38.014 --> 1:18:39.647
He's a good guy.

1:18:41.117 --> 1:18:43.250
[phone rings]

1:18:43.319 --> 1:18:45.786
Is that?

1:18:45.822 --> 1:18:46.854
Is it?

1:18:46.923 --> 1:18:47.788
It's from Vanessa.

1:18:47.824 --> 1:18:48.556
Uh-huh.

1:18:48.591 --> 1:18:49.390
What does it say?

1:18:49.425 --> 1:18:51.859
"Have you checked your email?"

1:18:51.894 --> 1:18:52.660
Let's check.

1:18:52.695 --> 1:18:53.994
Uh-huh.

1:18:54.464 --> 1:18:55.129
I don't know, Dad.

1:18:55.164 --> 1:18:56.931
I'm trying, I'm trying.

1:18:56.966 --> 1:18:58.933
It must be a large file.

1:19:01.170 --> 1:19:02.737
Okay, uh, thank you
for capturing

1:19:02.772 --> 1:19:04.972
the guiding light of Christmas.

1:19:05.007 --> 1:19:06.574
Uh-huh, uh-huh.

1:19:07.944 --> 1:19:08.776
You got it.

1:19:08.845 --> 1:19:09.443
You got it?

1:19:09.479 --> 1:19:09.977
I got it.

1:19:10.012 --> 1:19:10.845
You got it!

1:19:10.880 --> 1:19:11.445
[yells] You got it!

1:19:11.481 --> 1:19:11.979
I got it!

1:19:12.014 --> 1:19:12.680
You got it!

1:19:12.715 --> 1:19:13.414
Yes!

1:19:13.449 --> 1:19:14.248
You got it!

1:19:14.283 --> 1:19:15.316
[yelling, cheering]

1:19:15.384 --> 1:19:16.550
Does that mean you get
the job, too?

1:19:16.586 --> 1:19:20.287
Yeah, I mean, I guess so,
yeah!

1:19:20.323 --> 1:19:22.757
If I want it, yeah.

1:19:28.731 --> 1:19:35.703
I had a really good tour guide,
didn't I?

1:19:35.738 --> 1:19:37.805
You had an excellent guide.

1:19:40.343 --> 1:19:43.144
Sweetie?

1:19:43.179 --> 1:19:50.117
You deserve love
as well as success.

1:19:50.153 --> 1:19:53.187
I gotta go.

1:19:53.222 --> 1:19:54.388
Yeah, I gotta go!

1:19:54.423 --> 1:19:55.890
[laughs]

1:19:57.326 --> 1:19:58.726
Oh, wow.

1:20:08.538 --> 1:20:09.069
I'm sorry.

1:20:09.105 --> 1:20:10.571
What?

1:20:10.606 --> 1:20:12.573
I had to give you this.

1:20:17.580 --> 1:20:20.648
Every tour needs a souvenir,
right?

1:20:20.683 --> 1:20:22.383
This is mine.

1:20:27.223 --> 1:20:29.356
I'm so sorry about yesterday.

1:20:29.392 --> 1:20:31.392
No.

1:20:33.362 --> 1:20:38.866
I'm scared.

1:20:38.901 --> 1:20:41.268
I don't want to miss out
on our chance again.

1:20:41.304 --> 1:20:43.771
'Cause this is what I want.

1:20:43.806 --> 1:20:45.306
All of it.

1:20:45.341 --> 1:20:49.543
And you helped me see that.

1:20:49.612 --> 1:20:53.747
Well then, that would be pretty
awful to walk away from.

1:21:07.230 --> 1:21:09.964
Did you...

1:21:09.999 --> 1:21:11.732
...get the job?

1:21:11.767 --> 1:21:12.333
Mm-hmm.

1:21:12.368 --> 1:21:12.700
Yes.

1:21:12.735 --> 1:21:13.334
Yeah.

1:21:13.369 --> 1:21:14.301
Of course you did.

1:21:14.337 --> 1:21:15.035
Why didn't you tell me earlier?

1:21:15.071 --> 1:21:16.036
Congrats.

1:21:16.105 --> 1:21:16.837
Thanks.

1:21:16.873 --> 1:21:18.572
[laughs]

1:21:19.275 --> 1:21:21.876
Okay, does that mean
that you need to...

1:21:21.911 --> 1:21:23.010
Get back?

1:21:23.045 --> 1:21:25.379
Yeah.

1:21:25.448 --> 1:21:27.081
No.

1:21:27.717 --> 1:21:28.949
So?

1:21:28.985 --> 1:21:31.318
You're gonna keep freelancing?

1:21:31.354 --> 1:21:33.053
Mm-hmm.

1:21:34.857 --> 1:21:36.924
Well if... if I'm staying,

1:21:36.959 --> 1:21:39.193
and you're just gonna roll
with it, then, uh?

1:21:39.228 --> 1:21:40.661
Hmm.

1:21:40.696 --> 1:21:42.863
Looks like our timing
is improving.

1:21:42.932 --> 1:21:43.998
Yeah, it's about time.

1:21:44.033 --> 1:21:46.033
[laughs]

1:21:55.745 --> 1:21:58.712
You ready for the final stop
on our tour?

1:21:58.748 --> 1:22:00.047
Yeah.

1:22:04.921 --> 1:22:06.921
Okay, so, it's a choir?

1:22:06.989 --> 1:22:09.490
Nnn... not exactly.

1:22:09.525 --> 1:22:11.725
Come on, are you really
not gonna tell me again?

1:22:11.761 --> 1:22:14.261
I promise you it is worth
the wait.

1:22:14.297 --> 1:22:18.632
[bell chimes loudly]

1:22:28.978 --> 1:22:30.945
[bell chimes loudly]

1:22:30.980 --> 1:22:36.216
[more bells chime in]
♪

1:22:36.285 --> 1:22:46.293
<i> [Bell choir plays</i>
<i> "Joy to the World"]</i>
♪

1:22:46.329 --> 1:22:47.294
If the bells are ringing,

1:22:47.330 --> 1:22:49.129
does that mean I get
to make a wish?

1:22:49.198 --> 1:22:51.865
Absolutely.

1:22:51.901 --> 1:23:03.610
<i> [Bell choir plays</i>
<i> "Joy to the World"]</i>
♪

1:23:03.646 --> 1:23:05.312
Merry Christmas.

1:23:05.381 --> 1:23:18.025
♪
